15 #Generic LAPACK error handlers
16 """
17 Handle only negative LAPACK error codes
18
19 *NOTE* use only if the positive error code is useful.
20 """
21 function chkargsok(ret::BlasInt)
22 if ret < 0
23 throw(ArgumentError("invalid argument #$(-ret) to LAPACK call"))
24 end
25 end
26
27 "Handle all nonzero info codes"
28 function chklapackerror(ret::BlasInt)
29 if ret == 0
30 return
31 elseif ret < 0
32 throw(ArgumentError("invalid argument #$(-ret) to LAPACK call"))
33 else # ret > 0
34 throw(LAPACKException(ret))
35 end
36 end
37
38 function chknonsingular(ret::BlasInt)
39 if ret > 0
40 throw(SingularException(ret))
41 end
42 end
43
44 function chkposdef(ret::BlasInt)
45 if ret > 0
46 throw(PosDefException(ret))
47 end
48 end
49
50 "Check that upper/lower (for special matrices) is correctly specified"
51 function chkuplo(uplo::Char)
52 if !(uplo == 'U' || uplo == 'L')
53 throw(ArgumentError("uplo argument must be 'U' (upper) or 'L' (lower), got $uplo"))
54 end
55 uplo
56 end
57
58 "Check that {c}transpose is correctly specified"
59 function chktrans(trans::Char)
60 if !(trans == 'N' || trans == 'C' || trans == 'T')
61 throw(ArgumentError("trans argument must be 'N' (no transpose), 'T' (transpose), or 'C' (conjugate transpose), got $trans"))
62 end
63 trans
64 end
65
66 "Check that left/right hand side multiply is correctly specified"
67 function chkside(side::Char)
68 if !(side == 'L' || side == 'R')
69 throw(ArgumentError("side argument must be 'L' (left hand multiply) or 'R' (right hand multiply), got $side"))
70 end
71 side
72 end
73
74 "Check that unit diagonal flag is correctly specified"
75 function chkdiag(diag::Char)
76 if !(diag == 'U' || diag =='N')
77 throw(ArgumentError("diag argument must be 'U' (unit diagonal) or 'N' (non-unit diagonal), got $diag"))
78 end
79 diag
80 end
81
82 subsetrows(X::AbstractVector, Y::AbstractArray, k) = Y[1:k]
83 subsetrows(X::AbstractMatrix, Y::AbstractArray, k) = Y[1:k, :]
84
85 function chkfinite(A::StridedMatrix)
86 for a in A
87 if !isfinite(a)
88 throw(ArgumentError("matrix contains Infs or NaNs"))
89 end
90 end
91 return true
92 end
93
94 # LAPACK version number
95 function laver()
96 major = Ref{BlasInt}(0)
97 minor = Ref{BlasInt}(0)
98 patch = Ref{BlasInt}(0)
99 ccall((@blasfunc(ilaver_), liblapack), Void,
100 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
101 major, minor, patch)
102 return major[], minor[], patch[]
103 end

117 # DOUBLE PRECISION AB( LDAB, * )
118 function gbtrf!(kl::Integer, ku::Integer, m::Integer, AB::StridedMatrix{$elty})
119 chkstride1(AB)

121 mnmn = min(m, n)

123 info = Ref{BlasInt}()

130 end

156 B

161 """
162 gbtrf!(kl, ku, m, AB) -> (AB, ipiv)
163
164 Compute the LU factorization of a banded matrix `AB`. `kl` is the first
165 subdiagonal containing a nonzero band, `ku` is the last superdiagonal
166 containing one, and `m` is the first dimension of the matrix `AB`. Returns
167 the LU factorization in-place and `ipiv`, the vector of pivots used.
168 """
169 gbtrf!(kl::Integer, ku::Integer, m::Integer, AB::StridedMatrix)
170
171 """
172 gbtrs!(trans, kl, ku, m, AB, ipiv, B)
173
174 Solve the equation `AB * X = B`. `trans` determines the orientation of `AB`. It may
175 be `N` (no transpose), `T` (transpose), or `C` (conjugate transpose). `kl` is the
176 first subdiagonal containing a nonzero band, `ku` is the last superdiagonal
177 containing one, and `m` is the first dimension of the matrix `AB`. `ipiv` is the vector
178 of pivots returned from `gbtrf!`. Returns the vector or matrix `X`, overwriting `B` in-place.
179 """
180 gbtrs!(trans::Char, kl::Integer, ku::Integer, m::Integer, AB::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt}, B::StridedVecOrMat)
181
182 ## (GE) general matrices: balancing and back-transforming
183 for (gebal, gebak, elty, relty) in
184 ((:dgebal_, :dgebak_, :Float64, :Float64),
185 (:sgebal_, :sgebak_, :Float32, :Float32),
186 (:zgebal_, :zgebak_, :Complex128, :Float64),
187 (:cgebal_, :cgebak_, :Complex64, :Float32))
188 @eval begin
189 # SUBROUTINE DGEBAL( JOB, N, A, LDA, ILO, IHI, SCALE, INFO )
190 #* .. Scalar Arguments ..
191 # CHARACTER JOB
192 # INTEGER IHI, ILP, INFO, LDA, N
193 # .. Array Arguments ..
194 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), SCALE( * )
195 function gebal!(job::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
196 chkstride1(A)
197 n = checksquare(A)
198 chkfinite(A) # balancing routines don't support NaNs and Infs
199 ihi = Ref{BlasInt}()
200 ilo = Ref{BlasInt}()
201 scale = similar(A, $relty, n)
202 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
203 ccall((@blasfunc($gebal), liblapack), Void,
204 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
205 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
206 &job, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), ilo, ihi, scale, info)
207 chklapackerror(info[])
208 ilo[], ihi[], scale
209 end

211 # SUBROUTINE DGEBAK( JOB, SIDE, N, ILO, IHI, SCALE, M, V, LDV, INFO )
212 #* .. Scalar Arguments ..
213 # CHARACTER JOB, SIDE
214 # INTEGER IHI, ILP, INFO, LDV, M, N
215 # .. Array Arguments ..
216 # DOUBLE PRECISION SCALE( * ), V( LDV, * )
217 function gebak!(job::Char, side::Char,
218 ilo::BlasInt, ihi::BlasInt, scale::StridedVector{$relty},
219 V::StridedMatrix{$elty})
220 chkstride1(scale, V)
221 chkside(side)
222 chkfinite(V) # balancing routines don't support NaNs and Infs
223 n = checksquare(V)
224 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
225 ccall((@blasfunc($gebak), liblapack), Void,
226 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
227 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
228 &job, &side, &size(V,1), &ilo, &ihi, scale, &n, V, &max(1,stride(V,2)), info)
229 chklapackerror(info[])
230 V
231 end
232 end
233 end

235 """
236 gebal!(job, A) -> (ilo, ihi, scale)
237
238 Balance the matrix `A` before computing its eigensystem or Schur factorization.
239 `job` can be one of `N` (`A` will not be permuted or scaled), `P` (`A` will only
240 be permuted), `S` (`A` will only be scaled), or `B` (`A` will be both permuted
241 and scaled). Modifies `A` in-place and returns `ilo`, `ihi`, and `scale`. If
242 permuting was turned on, `A[i,j] = 0` if `j > i` and `1 < j < ilo` or `j > ihi`.
243 `scale` contains information about the scaling/permutations performed.
244 """
245 gebal!(job::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
246
247 """
248 gebak!(job, side, ilo, ihi, scale, V)
249
250 Transform the eigenvectors `V` of a matrix balanced using `gebal!` to
251 the unscaled/unpermuted eigenvectors of the original matrix. Modifies `V`
252 in-place. `side` can be `L` (left eigenvectors are transformed) or `R`
253 (right eigenvectors are transformed).
254 """
255 gebak!(job::Char, side::Char, ilo::BlasInt, ihi::BlasInt, scale::StridedVector, V::StridedMatrix)
256
257 # (GE) general matrices, direct decompositions
258 #
259 # These mutating functions take as arguments all the values they
260 # return, even if the value of the function does not depend on them
261 # (e.g. the tau argument). This is so that a factorization can be
262 # updated in place. The condensed mutating functions, usually a
263 # function of A only, are defined after this block.
264 for (gebrd, gelqf, geqlf, geqrf, geqp3, geqrt, geqrt3, gerqf, getrf, elty, relty) in
265 ((:dgebrd_,:dgelqf_,:dgeqlf_,:dgeqrf_,:dgeqp3_,:dgeqrt_,:dgeqrt3_,:dgerqf_,:dgetrf_,:Float64,:Float64),
266 (:sgebrd_,:sgelqf_,:sgeqlf_,:sgeqrf_,:sgeqp3_,:sgeqrt_,:sgeqrt3_,:sgerqf_,:sgetrf_,:Float32,:Float32),
267 (:zgebrd_,:zgelqf_,:zgeqlf_,:zgeqrf_,:zgeqp3_,:zgeqrt_,:zgeqrt3_,:zgerqf_,:zgetrf_,:Complex128,:Float64),
268 (:cgebrd_,:cgelqf_,:cgeqlf_,:cgeqrf_,:cgeqp3_,:cgeqrt_,:cgeqrt3_,:cgerqf_,:cgetrf_,:Complex64,:Float32))
269 @eval begin
270 # SUBROUTINE DGEBRD( M, N, A, LDA, D, E, TAUQ, TAUP, WORK, LWORK,
271 # INFO )
272 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
273 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LWORK, M, N
274 # .. Array Arguments ..
275 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), D( * ), E( * ), TAUP( * ),
276 # TAUQ( * ), WORK( * )
277 function gebrd!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
278 chkstride1(A)
279 m, n = size(A)
280 k = min(m, n)
281 d = similar(A, $relty, k)
282 e = similar(A, $relty, k)
283 tauq = similar(A, $elty, k)
284 taup = similar(A, $elty, k)
285 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
286 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
287 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
288 for i = 1:2
289 ccall((@blasfunc($gebrd), liblapack), Void,
290 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
291 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
292 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
293 &m, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)),
294 d, e, tauq, taup,
295 work, &lwork, info)
296 chklapackerror(info[])
297 if i == 1
298 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
299 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
300 end
301 end
302 A, d, e, tauq, taup
303 end

365 # SUBROUTINE DGEQP3( M, N, A, LDA, JPVT, TAU, WORK, LWORK, INFO )
366 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
367 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LWORK, M, N
368 # * .. Array Arguments ..
369 # INTEGER JPVT( * )
370 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), TAU( * ), WORK( * )
371 function geqp3!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, jpvt::StridedVector{BlasInt}, tau::StridedVector{$elty})
372 chkstride1(A,jpvt,tau)
373 m,n = size(A)
374 if length(tau) != min(m,n)
375 throw(DimensionMismatch("tau has length $(length(tau)), but needs length $(min(m,n))"))
376 end
377 if length(jpvt) != n
378 throw(DimensionMismatch("jpvt has length $(length(jpvt)), but needs length $n"))
379 end
380 lda = stride(A,2)
381 if lda == 0
382 return A, tau, jpvt
383 end # Early exit
384 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
385 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
386 cmplx = eltype(A)<:Complex
387 if cmplx
388 rwork = Vector{$relty}(2n)
389 end
390 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
391 for i = 1:2
392 if cmplx
393 ccall((@blasfunc($geqp3), liblapack), Void,
394 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
395 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
396 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
397 &m, &n, A, &lda,
398 jpvt, tau, work, &lwork,
399 rwork, info)
400 else
401 ccall((@blasfunc($geqp3), liblapack), Void,
402 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
403 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
404 Ptr{BlasInt}),
405 &m, &n, A, &lda,
406 jpvt, tau, work,
407 &lwork, info)
408 end
409 chklapackerror(info[])
410 if i == 1
411 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
412 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
413 end
414 end
415 return A, tau, jpvt
416 end

418 function geqrt!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, T::StridedMatrix{$elty})
419 chkstride1(A)
420 m, n = size(A)
421 minmn = min(m, n)
422 nb = size(T, 1)
423 if nb > minmn
424 throw(ArgumentError("block size $nb > $minmn too large"))
425 end
426 lda = max(1, stride(A,2))
427 work = Vector{$elty}(nb*n)
428 if n > 0
429 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
430 ccall((@blasfunc($geqrt), liblapack), Void,
431 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
432 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
433 Ptr{BlasInt}),
434 &m, &n, &nb, A,
435 &lda, T, &max(1,stride(T,2)), work,
436 info)
437 chklapackerror(info[])
438 end
439 A, T
440 end

442 function geqrt3!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, T::StridedMatrix{$elty})
443 chkstride1(A)
444 chkstride1(T)
445 m, n = size(A)
446 p, q = size(T)
447 if m < n
448 throw(DimensionMismatch("input matrix A has dimensions ($m,$n), but should have more rows than columns"))
449 end
450 if p != n || q != n
451 throw(DimensionMismatch("block reflector T has dimensions ($p,$q), but should have dimensions ($n,$n)"))
452 end
453 if n > 0
454 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
455 ccall((@blasfunc($geqrt3), liblapack), Void,
456 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
457 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
458 &m, &n, A, &max(1, stride(A, 2)),
459 T, &max(1,stride(T,2)), info)
460 chklapackerror(info[])
461 end
462 A, T
463 end

544 """
545 gebrd!(A) -> (A, d, e, tauq, taup)
546
547 Reduce `A` in-place to bidiagonal form `A = QBP'`. Returns `A`, containing the
548 bidiagonal matrix `B`; `d`, containing the diagonal elements of `B`; `e`,
549 containing the off-diagonal elements of `B`; `tauq`, containing the
550 elementary reflectors representing `Q`; and `taup`, containing the
551 elementary reflectors representing `P`.
552 """
553 gebrd!(A::StridedMatrix)

754 function tzrzf!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
755 m, n = size(A)
756 if n < m
757 throw(DimensionMismatch("input matrix A has dimensions ($m,$n), but cannot have fewer columns than rows"))
758 end

760 tau = similar(A, $elty, m)

770 chklapackerror(info[])

772 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
773 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
774 end
775 end
776 A, tau
777 end

843 ## (GE) general matrices, solvers with factorization, solver and inverse
844 for (gels, gesv, getrs, getri, elty) in
845 ((:dgels_,:dgesv_,:dgetrs_,:dgetri_,:Float64),
846 (:sgels_,:sgesv_,:sgetrs_,:sgetri_,:Float32),
847 (:zgels_,:zgesv_,:zgetrs_,:zgetri_,:Complex128),
848 (:cgels_,:cgesv_,:cgetrs_,:cgetri_,:Complex64))
849 @eval begin
850 # SUBROUTINE DGELS( TRANS, M, N, NRHS, A, LDA, B, LDB, WORK, LWORK,INFO)
851 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
852 # CHARACTER TRANS
853 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LWORK, M, N, NRHS
854 function gels!(trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
855 chktrans(trans)
856 chkstride1(A, B)
857 btrn = trans == 'T'
858 m, n = size(A)
859 if size(B,1) != (btrn ? n : m)
860 throw(DimensionMismatch("matrix A has dimensions ($m,$n), transposed: $btrn, but leading dimension of B is $(size(B,1))"))
861 end
862 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
863 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
864 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
865 for i = 1:2
866 ccall((@blasfunc($gels), liblapack), Void,
867 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
868 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
869 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
870 &(btrn?'T':'N'), &m, &n, &size(B,2), A, &max(1,stride(A,2)),
871 B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), work, &lwork, info)
872 chklapackerror(info[])
873 if i == 1
874 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
875 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
876 end
877 end
878 k = min(m, n)
879 F = m < n ? tril(A[1:k, 1:k]) : triu(A[1:k, 1:k])
880 ssr = Vector{$elty}(size(B, 2))
881 for i = 1:size(B,2)
882 x = zero($elty)
883 for j = k+1:size(B,1)
884 x += abs2(B[j,i])
885 end
886 ssr[i] = x
887 end
888 F, subsetrows(B, B, k), ssr
889 end

891 # SUBROUTINE DGESV( N, NRHS, A, LDA, IPIV, B, LDB, INFO )

895 # * .. Array Arguments ..

904 ipiv = similar(A, BlasInt, n)
905 info = Ref{BlasInt}()

908 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
909 &n, &size(B,2), A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), ipiv, B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), info)
910 chklapackerror(info[])

912 end

970 """
971 gels!(trans, A, B) -> (F, B, ssr)
972
973 Solves the linear equation `A * X = B`, `A.' * X =B`, or `A' * X = B` using
974 a QR or LQ factorization. Modifies the matrix/vector `B` in place with the
975 solution. `A` is overwritten with its `QR` or `LQ` factorization. `trans`
976 may be one of `N` (no modification), `T` (transpose), or `C` (conjugate
977 transpose). `gels!` searches for the minimum norm/least squares solution.
978 `A` may be under or over determined. The solution is returned in `B`.
979 """
980 gels!(trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat)
981
982 """
983 gesv!(A, B) -> (B, A, ipiv)
984
985 Solves the linear equation `A * X = B` where `A` is a square matrix using
986 the `LU` factorization of `A`. `A` is overwritten with its `LU`
987 factorization and `B` is overwritten with the solution `X`. `ipiv` contains the
988 pivoting information for the `LU` factorization of `A`.
989 """
990 gesv!(A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat)
991
992 """
993 getrs!(trans, A, ipiv, B)
994
995 Solves the linear equation `A * X = B`, `A.' * X =B`, or `A' * X = B` for
996 square `A`. Modifies the matrix/vector `B` in place with the solution. `A`
997 is the `LU` factorization from `getrf!`, with `ipiv` the pivoting
998 information. `trans` may be one of `N` (no modification), `T` (transpose),
999 or `C` (conjugate transpose).
1000 """
1001 getrs!(trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt}, B::StridedVecOrMat)

1003 """
1004 getri!(A, ipiv)
1005
1006 Computes the inverse of `A`, using its `LU` factorization found by
1007 `getrf!`. `ipiv` is the pivot information output and `A`
1008 contains the `LU` factorization of `getrf!`. `A` is overwritten with
1009 its inverse.
1010 """
1011 getri!(A::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt})
1012
1013 for (gesvx, elty) in
1014 ((:dgesvx_,:Float64),
1015 (:sgesvx_,:Float32))
1016 @eval begin
1017 # SUBROUTINE DGESVX( FACT, TRANS, N, NRHS, A, LDA, AF, LDAF, IPIV,
1018 # EQUED, R, C, B, LDB, X, LDX, RCOND, FERR, BERR,
1019 # WORK, IWORK, INFO )

1021 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
1022 # CHARACTER EQUED, FACT, TRANS
1023 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDAF, LDB, LDX, N, NRHS
1024 # DOUBLE PRECISION RCOND
1025 # ..
1026 # .. Array Arguments ..
1027 # INTEGER IPIV( * ), IWORK( * )
1028 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), AF( LDAF, * ), B( LDB, * ),
1029 # $ BERR( * ), C( * ), FERR( * ), R( * ),
1030 # $ WORK( * ), X( LDX, *
1031 #
1032 function gesvx!(fact::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty},
1033 AF::StridedMatrix{$elty}, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt}, equed::Char,
1034 R::StridedVector{$elty}, C::StridedVector{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
1035 chktrans(trans)
1036 chkstride1(ipiv, R, C)
1037 n = checksquare(A)
1038 lda = stride(A,2)
1039 n = checksquare(AF)
1040 ldaf = stride(AF,2)
1041 nrhs = size(B,2)
1042 ldb = stride(B,2)
1043 rcond = Vector{$elty}(1)
1044 ferr = similar(A, $elty, nrhs)
1045 berr = similar(A, $elty, nrhs)
1046 work = Vector{$elty}(4n)
1047 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(n)
1048 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1049 X = similar(A, $elty, n, nrhs)
1050 ccall((@blasfunc($gesvx), liblapack), Void,
1051 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1052 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1053 Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1054 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
1055 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1056 &fact, &trans, &n, &nrhs, A, &lda, AF, &ldaf, ipiv, &equed, R, C, B,
1057 &ldb, X, &n, rcond, ferr, berr, work, iwork, info)
1058 chklapackerror(info[])
1059 if info[] == n + 1
1060 warn("matrix is singular to working precision")
1061 else
1062 chknonsingular(info[])
1063 end
1064 #WORK(1) contains the reciprocal pivot growth factor norm(A)/norm(U)
1065 X, equed, R, C, B, rcond[1], ferr, berr, work[1]
1066 end

1068 function gesvx!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
1069 n = size(A,1)
1070 X, equed, R, C, B, rcond, ferr, berr, rpgf =
1071 gesvx!('N', 'N', A,
1072 similar(A, $elty, n, n),
1073 similar(A, BlasInt, n),
1074 'N',
1075 similar(A, $elty, n),
1076 similar(A, $elty, n),
1077 B)
1078 X, rcond, ferr, berr, rpgf
1079 end
1080 end

1086 # SUBROUTINE ZGESVX( FACT, TRANS, N, NRHS, A, LDA, AF, LDAF, IPIV,
1087 # EQUED, R, C, B, LDB, X, LDX, RCOND, FERR, BERR,
1088 # WORK, RWORK, INFO )
1089 #
1090 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
1091 # CHARACTER EQUED, FACT, TRANS
1092 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDAF, LDB, LDX, N, NRHS
1093 # DOUBLE PRECISION RCOND
1094 # ..
1095 # .. Array Arguments ..
1096 # INTEGER IPIV( * )
1097 # DOUBLE PRECISION BERR( * ), C( * ), FERR( * ), R( * ),
1098 # $ RWORK( * )
1099 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), AF( LDAF, * ), B( LDB, * ),
1100 # $ WORK( * ), X( LDX, * )
1101 function gesvx!(fact::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty},
1102 AF::StridedMatrix{$elty}, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt}, equed::Char,
1103 R::StridedVector{$relty}, C::StridedVector{$relty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
1104 chktrans(trans)
1105 chkstride1(ipiv, R, C)
1106 n = checksquare(A)
1107 lda = stride(A,2)
1108 n = checksquare(AF)
1109 ldaf = stride(AF,2)
1110 nrhs = size(B,2)
1111 ldb = stride(B,2)
1112 rcond = Vector{$relty}(1)
1113 ferr = similar(A, $relty, nrhs)
1114 berr = similar(A, $relty, nrhs)
1115 work = Vector{$elty}(2n)
1116 rwork = Vector{$relty}(2n)
1117 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1118 X = similar(A, $elty, n, nrhs)
1119 ccall((@blasfunc($gesvx), liblapack), Void,
1120 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1121 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1122 Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1123 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty},
1124 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1125 &fact, &trans, &n, &nrhs, A, &lda, AF, &ldaf, ipiv, &equed, R, C, B,
1126 &ldb, X, &n, rcond, ferr, berr, work, rwork, info)
1127 chklapackerror(info[])
1128 if info[] == n + 1
1129 warn("matrix is singular to working precision")
1130 else
1131 chknonsingular(info[])
1132 end
1133 #RWORK(1) contains the reciprocal pivot growth factor norm(A)/norm(U)
1134 X, equed, R, C, B, rcond[1], ferr, berr, rwork[1]
1135 end
1136
1137 #Wrapper for the no-equilibration, no-transpose calculation
1138 function gesvx!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
1139 n = size(A,1)
1140 X, equed, R, C, B, rcond, ferr, berr, rpgf =
1141 gesvx!('N', 'N', A,
1142 similar(A, $elty, n, n),
1143 similar(A, BlasInt, n),
1144 'N',
1145 similar(A, $relty, n),
1146 similar(A, $relty, n),
1147 B)
1148 X, rcond, ferr, berr, rpgf
1149 end
1150 end
1151 end
1152
1153 """
1154 gesvx!(fact, trans, A, AF, ipiv, equed, R, C, B) -> (X, equed, R, C, B, rcond, ferr, berr, work)
1155
1156 Solves the linear equation `A * X = B` (`trans = N`), `A.' * X =B`
1157 (`trans = T`), or `A' * X = B` (`trans = C`) using the `LU` factorization
1158 of `A`. `fact` may be `E`, in which case `A` will be equilibrated and copied
1159 to `AF`; `F`, in which case `AF` and `ipiv` from a previous `LU` factorization
1160 are inputs; or `N`, in which case `A` will be copied to `AF` and then
1161 factored. If `fact = F`, `equed` may be `N`, meaning `A` has not been
1162 equilibrated; `R`, meaning `A` was multiplied by `diagm(R)` from the left;
1163 `C`, meaning `A` was multiplied by `diagm(C)` from the right; or `B`, meaning
1164 `A` was multiplied by `diagm(R)` from the left and `diagm(C)` from the right.
1165 If `fact = F` and `equed = R` or `B` the elements of `R` must all be positive.
1166 If `fact = F` and `equed = C` or `B` the elements of `C` must all be positive.
1167
1168 Returns the solution `X`; `equed`, which is an output if `fact` is not `N`,
1169 and describes the equilibration that was performed; `R`, the row equilibration
1170 diagonal; `C`, the column equilibration diagonal; `B`, which may be overwritten
1171 with its equilibrated form `diagm(R)*B` (if `trans = N` and `equed = R,B`) or
1172 `diagm(C)*B` (if `trans = T,C` and `equed = C,B`); `rcond`, the reciprocal
1173 condition number of `A` after equilbrating; `ferr`, the forward error bound for
1174 each solution vector in `X`; `berr`, the forward error bound for each solution
1175 vector in `X`; and `work`, the reciprocal pivot growth factor.
1176 """
1177 gesvx!(fact::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, AF::StridedMatrix,
1178 ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt}, equed::Char, R::StridedVector, C::StridedVector, B::StridedVecOrMat)
1179
1180 """
1181 gesvx!(A, B)
1182
1183 The no-equilibration, no-transpose simplification of `gesvx!`.
1184 """
1185 gesvx!(A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat)
1186
1187 for (gelsd, gelsy, elty) in
1188 ((:dgelsd_,:dgelsy_,:Float64),
1189 (:sgelsd_,:sgelsy_,:Float32))
1190 @eval begin
1191 # SUBROUTINE DGELSD( M, N, NRHS, A, LDA, B, LDB, S, RCOND, RANK,
1192 # $ WORK, LWORK, IWORK, INFO )

1194 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LWORK, M, N, NRHS, RANK

1196 # * ..
1197 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1198 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
1199 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), S( * ), WORK( * )
1200 function gelsd!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty}, rcond::Real=-one($elty))
1201 chkstride1(A, B)
1202 m, n = size(A)
1203 if size(B, 1) != m
1204 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has leading dimension $(size(B,1)) but needs $m"))
1205 end
1206 newB = [B; zeros($elty, max(0, n - size(B, 1)), size(B, 2))]
1207 s = similar(A, $elty, min(m, n))

1209 rnk = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
1210 info = Ref{BlasInt}()

1212 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1213 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
1214 for i = 1:2

1216 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1217 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1218 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1219 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1220 &m, &n, &size(B,2), A, &max(1,stride(A,2)),
1221 newB, &max(1,stride(B,2),n), s, &rcond, rnk, work, &lwork, iwork, info)
1222 chklapackerror(info[])
1223 if i == 1
1224 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
1225 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1226 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(iwork[1])
1227 end
1228 end
1229 subsetrows(B, newB, n), rnk[1]
1230 end
1231
1232 # SUBROUTINE DGELSY( M, N, NRHS, A, LDA, B, LDB, JPVT, RCOND, RANK,
1233 # $ WORK, LWORK, INFO )
1234 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
1235 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LWORK, M, N, NRHS, RANK
1236 # DOUBLE PRECISION RCOND
1237 # * ..
1238 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1239 # INTEGER JPVT( * )
1240 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), WORK( * )
1241 function gelsy!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty}, rcond::Real=eps($elty))

1244 n = size(A, 2)
1245 nrhs = size(B, 2)
1246 if size(B, 1) != m
1247 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has leading dimension $(size(B,1)) but needs $m"))
1248 end
1249 newB = [B; zeros($elty, max(0, n - size(B, 1)), size(B, 2))]
1250 lda = max(1, m)
1251 ldb = max(1, m, n)
1252 jpvt = zeros(BlasInt, n)
1253 rcond = convert($elty, rcond)
1254 rnk = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
1255 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1256 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1257 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1258 for i = 1:2
1259 ccall((@blasfunc($gelsy), liblapack), Void,
1260 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1261 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1262 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1263 Ptr{BlasInt}),
1264 &m, &n, &nrhs, A,
1265 &lda, newB, &ldb, jpvt,
1266 &rcond, rnk, work, &lwork,
1267 info)
1268 chklapackerror(info[])
1269 if i == 1
1270 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
1271 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1272 end
1273 end
1274 subsetrows(B, newB, n), rnk[1]
1275 end
1276 end

1286 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LWORK, M, N, NRHS, RANK

1288 # * ..
1289 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1290 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
1291 # DOUBLE PRECISION RWORK( * ), S( * )
1292 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), WORK( * )
1293 function gelsd!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty}, rcond::Real=-one($relty))

1300 s = similar(A, $relty, min(m, n))
1301 rcond = convert($relty, rcond)

1312 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1313 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),

1315 newB, &max(1,stride(B,2),n), s, &rcond, rnk, work, &lwork, rwork, iwork, info)
1316 chklapackerror(info[])

1375 """
1376 gelsd!(A, B, rcond) -> (B, rnk)
1377
1378 Computes the least norm solution of `A * X = B` by finding the `SVD`
1379 factorization of `A`, then dividing-and-conquering the problem. `B`
1380 is overwritten with the solution `X`. Singular values below `rcond`
1381 will be treated as zero. Returns the solution in `B` and the effective rank
1382 of `A` in `rnk`.
1383 """
1384 gelsd!(A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat, rcond::Real)
1385
1386 """
1387 gelsy!(A, B, rcond) -> (B, rnk)
1388
1389 Computes the least norm solution of `A * X = B` by finding the full `QR`
1390 factorization of `A`, then dividing-and-conquering the problem. `B`
1391 is overwritten with the solution `X`. Singular values below `rcond`
1392 will be treated as zero. Returns the solution in `B` and the effective rank
1393 of `A` in `rnk`.
1394 """
1395 gelsy!(A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat, rcond::Real)
1396
1397 for (gglse, elty) in ((:dgglse_, :Float64),
1398 (:sgglse_, :Float32),
1399 (:zgglse_, :Complex128),
1400 (:cgglse_, :Complex64))
1401 @eval begin
1402 # SUBROUTINE DGGLSE( M, N, P, A, LDA, B, LDB, C, D, X, WORK, LWORK,
1403 # $ INFO )
1404 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
1405 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LWORK, M, N, P
1406 # * ..
1407 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1408 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), C( * ), D( * ),
1409 # $ WORK( * ), X( * )
1410 function gglse!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, c::StridedVector{$elty},
1411 B::StridedMatrix{$elty}, d::StridedVector{$elty})
1412 chkstride1(A, B)
1413 m, n = size(A)
1414 p = size(B, 1)
1415 if size(B, 2) != n
1416 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has second dimension $(size(B,2)), needs $n"))
1417 end
1418 if length(c) != m
1419 throw(DimensionMismatch("c has length $(length(c)), needs $m"))
1420 end
1421 if length(d) != p
1422 throw(DimensionMismatch("d has length $(length(d)), needs $p"))
1423 end
1424 X = zeros($elty, n)
1425 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1426 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1427 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1428 for i = 1:2
1429 ccall((@blasfunc($gglse), liblapack), Void,
1430 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1431 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1432 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1433 Ptr{BlasInt}),
1434 &m, &n, &p, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), c, d, X,
1435 work, &lwork, info)
1436 chklapackerror(info[])
1437 if i == 1
1438 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
1439 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1440 end
1441 end
1442 X, dot(view(c, n - p + 1:m), view(c, n - p + 1:m))
1443 end
1444 end
1445 end

1447 """
1448 gglse!(A, c, B, d) -> (X,res)
1449
1450 Solves the equation `A * x = c` where `x` is subject to the equality
1451 constraint `B * x = d`. Uses the formula `||c - A*x||^2 = 0` to solve.
1452 Returns `X` and the residual sum-of-squares.
1453 """
1454 gglse!(A::StridedMatrix, c::StridedVector, B::StridedMatrix, d::StridedVector)
1455
1456 # (GE) general matrices eigenvalue-eigenvector and singular value decompositions
1457 for (geev, gesvd, gesdd, ggsvd, elty, relty) in
1458 ((:dgeev_,:dgesvd_,:dgesdd_,:dggsvd_,:Float64,:Float64),
1459 (:sgeev_,:sgesvd_,:sgesdd_,:sggsvd_,:Float32,:Float32),
1460 (:zgeev_,:zgesvd_,:zgesdd_,:zggsvd_,:Complex128,:Float64),
1461 (:cgeev_,:cgesvd_,:cgesdd_,:cggsvd_,:Complex64,:Float32))
1462 @eval begin
1463 # SUBROUTINE DGEEV( JOBVL, JOBVR, N, A, LDA, WR, WI, VL, LDVL, VR,
1464 # $ LDVR, WORK, LWORK, INFO )
1465 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
1466 # CHARACTER JOBVL, JOBVR
1467 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDVL, LDVR, LWORK, N
1468 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1469 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), VL( LDVL, * ), VR( LDVR, * ),
1470 # $ WI( * ), WORK( * ), WR( * )
1471 function geev!(jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
1472 chkstride1(A)
1473 n = checksquare(A)
1474 chkfinite(A) # balancing routines don't support NaNs and Infs
1475 lvecs = jobvl == 'V'
1476 rvecs = jobvr == 'V'
1477 VL = similar(A, $elty, (n, lvecs ? n : 0))
1478 VR = similar(A, $elty, (n, rvecs ? n : 0))
1479 cmplx = eltype(A) <: Complex
1480 if cmplx
1481 W = similar(A, $elty, n)
1482 rwork = similar(A, $relty, 2n)
1483 else
1484 WR = similar(A, $elty, n)
1485 WI = similar(A, $elty, n)
1486 end
1487 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1488 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1489 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1490 for i = 1:2
1491 if cmplx
1492 ccall((@blasfunc($geev), liblapack), Void,
1493 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1494 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1495 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1496 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1497 &jobvl, &jobvr, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), W, VL, &n, VR, &n,
1498 work, &lwork, rwork, info)
1499 else
1500 ccall((@blasfunc($geev), liblapack), Void,
1501 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1502 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
1503 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1504 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1505 &jobvl, &jobvr, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), WR, WI, VL, &n,
1506 VR, &n, work, &lwork, info)
1507 end
1508 chklapackerror(info[])
1509 if i == 1
1510 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
1511 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1512 end
1513 end
1514 cmplx ? (W, VL, VR) : (WR, WI, VL, VR)
1515 end
1516
1517 # SUBROUTINE DGESDD( JOBZ, M, N, A, LDA, S, U, LDU, VT, LDVT, WORK,
1518 # LWORK, IWORK, INFO )
1519 #* .. Scalar Arguments ..
1520 # CHARACTER JOBZ
1521 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDU, LDVT, LWORK, M, N
1522 #* ..
1523 #* .. Array Arguments ..
1524 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
1525 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), S( * ), U( LDU, * ),
1526 # VT( LDVT, * ), WORK( * )
1527 function gesdd!(job::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
1528 chkstride1(A)
1529 m, n = size(A)
1530 minmn = min(m, n)
1531 if job == 'A'
1532 U = similar(A, $elty, (m, m))
1533 VT = similar(A, $elty, (n, n))
1534 elseif job == 'S'
1535 U = similar(A, $elty, (m, minmn))
1536 VT = similar(A, $elty, (minmn, n))
1537 elseif job == 'O'
1538 U = similar(A, $elty, (m, m >= n ? 0 : m))
1539 VT = similar(A, $elty, (n, m >= n ? n : 0))
1540 else
1541 U = similar(A, $elty, (m, 0))
1542 VT = similar(A, $elty, (n, 0))
1543 end
1544 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1545 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1546 S = similar(A, $relty, minmn)
1547 cmplx = eltype(A)<:Complex
1548 if cmplx
1549 rwork = Array{$relty}(job == 'N' ? 7*minmn :
1550 minmn*max(5*minmn+7, 2*max(m,n)+2*minmn+1))
1551 end
1552 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(8*minmn)
1553 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1554 for i = 1:2
1555 if cmplx
1556 ccall((@blasfunc($gesdd), liblapack), Void,
1557 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1558 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1559 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1560 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1561 &job, &m, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), S, U, &max(1,stride(U,2)), VT, &max(1,stride(VT,2)),
1562 work, &lwork, rwork, iwork, info)
1563 else
1564 ccall((@blasfunc($gesdd), liblapack), Void,
1565 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1566 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1567 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1568 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1569 &job, &m, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), S, U, &max(1,stride(U,2)), VT, &max(1,stride(VT,2)),
1570 work, &lwork, iwork, info)
1571 end
1572 chklapackerror(info[])
1573 if i == 1
1574 # Work around issue with truncated Float32 representation of lwork in
1575 # sgesdd by using nextfloat. See
1576 # http://icl.cs.utk.edu/lapack-forum/viewtopic.php?f=13&t=4587&p=11036&hilit=sgesdd#p11036
1577 # and
1578 # https://github.com/scipy/scipy/issues/5401
1579 lwork = round(BlasInt, nextfloat(real(work[1])))
1580 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1581 end
1582 end
1583 if job == 'O'
1584 if m >= n
1585 return (A, S, VT)
1586 else
1587 # ()__
1588 # ||::Z__
1589 # ||::|:::Z____
1590 # ||::|:::|====|
1591 # ||==|===|====|
1592 # ||""|===|====|
1593 # || `"""|====|
1594 # || `""""`
1595 return (U, S, A)
1596 end
1597 end
1598 return (U, S, VT)
1599 end
1600
1601 # SUBROUTINE DGESVD( JOBU, JOBVT, M, N, A, LDA, S, U, LDU, VT, LDVT, WORK, LWORK, INFO )
1602 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
1603 # CHARACTER JOBU, JOBVT
1604 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDU, LDVT, LWORK, M, N
1605 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1606 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), S( * ), U( LDU, * ),
1607 # $ VT( LDVT, * ), WORK( * )
1608 function gesvd!(jobu::Char, jobvt::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
1609 chkstride1(A)
1610 m, n = size(A)
1611 minmn = min(m, n)
1612 S = similar(A, $relty, minmn)
1613 U = similar(A, $elty, jobu == 'A'? (m, m):(jobu == 'S'? (m, minmn) : (m, 0)))
1614 VT = similar(A, $elty, jobvt == 'A'? (n, n):(jobvt == 'S'? (minmn, n) : (n, 0)))
1615 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1616 cmplx = eltype(A) <: Complex
1617 if cmplx
1618 rwork = Vector{$relty}(5minmn)
1619 end
1620 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1621 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1622 for i in 1:2
1623 if cmplx
1624 ccall((@blasfunc($gesvd), liblapack), Void,
1625 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1626 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty},
1627 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1628 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1629 &jobu, &jobvt, &m, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), S, U, &max(1,stride(U,2)), VT, &max(1,stride(VT,2)),
1630 work, &lwork, rwork, info)
1631 else
1632 ccall((@blasfunc($gesvd), liblapack), Void,
1633 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1634 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
1635 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1636 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1637 &jobu, &jobvt, &m, &n, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), S, U, &max(1,stride(U,2)), VT, &max(1,stride(VT,2)),
1638 work, &lwork, info)
1639 end
1640 chklapackerror(info[])
1641 if i == 1
1642 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
1643 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1644 end
1645 end
1646 if jobu == 'O'
1647 return (A, S, VT)
1648 elseif jobvt == 'O'
1649 # =============|===========|()
1650 # # # #::::::
1651 # # # #::::::
1652 # # # #::::::
1653 # # # #::::::
1654 # # # # # # #
1655 # # # # # # #
1656 # # # # # # #
1657 return (U, S, A) # # # # # # #
1658 else # # # # # # #
1659 return (U, S, VT) # # # # # # #
1660
1661 end
1662 end
1663
1664 # SUBROUTINE ZGGSVD( JOBU, JOBV, JOBQ, M, N, P, K, L, A, LDA, B,
1665 # $ LDB, ALPHA, BETA, U, LDU, V, LDV, Q, LDQ, WORK,
1666 # $ RWORK, IWORK, INFO )
1667 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
1668 # CHARACTER JOBQ, JOBU, JOBV
1669 # INTEGER INFO, K, L, LDA, LDB, LDQ, LDU, LDV, M, N, P
1670 # * ..
1671 # * .. Array Arguments ..
1672 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
1673 # DOUBLE PRECISION ALPHA( * ), BETA( * ), RWORK( * )
1674 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), Q( LDQ, * ),
1675 # $ U( LDU, * ), V( LDV, * ), WORK( * )
1676 function ggsvd!(jobu::Char, jobv::Char, jobq::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedMatrix{$elty})
1677 chkstride1(A, B)
1678 m, n = size(A)
1679 if size(B, 2) != n
1680 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has second dimension $(size(B,2)) but needs $n"))
1681 end
1682 p = size(B, 1)
1683 k = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
1684 l = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
1685 lda = max(1,stride(A, 2))
1686 ldb = max(1,stride(B, 2))
1687 alpha = similar(A, $relty, n)
1688 beta = similar(A, $relty, n)
1689 ldu = max(1, m)
1690 U = jobu == 'U' ? similar(A, $elty, ldu, m) : similar(A, $elty, 0)
1691 ldv = max(1, p)
1692 V = jobv == 'V' ? similar(A, $elty, ldv, p) : similar(A, $elty, 0)
1693 ldq = max(1, n)
1694 Q = jobq == 'Q' ? similar(A, $elty, ldq, n) : similar(A, $elty, 0)
1695 work = Vector{$elty}(max(3n, m, p) + n)
1696 cmplx = eltype(A) <: Complex
1697 if cmplx
1698 rwork = Vector{$relty}(2n)
1699 end
1700 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(n)
1701 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1702 if cmplx
1703 ccall((@blasfunc($ggsvd), liblapack), Void,
1704 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1705 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1706 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1707 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1708 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1709 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1710 &jobu, &jobv, &jobq, &m,
1711 &n, &p, k, l,
1712 A, &lda, B, &ldb,
1713 alpha, beta, U, &ldu,
1714 V, &ldv, Q, &ldq,
1715 work, rwork, iwork, info)
1716 else
1717 ccall((@blasfunc($ggsvd), liblapack), Void,
1718 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1719 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1720 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1721 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1722 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1723 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1724 &jobu, &jobv, &jobq, &m,
1725 &n, &p, k, l,
1726 A, &lda, B, &ldb,
1727 alpha, beta, U, &ldu,
1728 V, &ldv, Q, &ldq,
1729 work, iwork, info)
1730 end
1731 chklapackerror(info[])
1732 if m - k[1] - l[1] >= 0
1733 R = triu(A[1:k[1] + l[1],n - k[1] - l[1] + 1:n])
1734 else
1735 R = triu([A[1:m, n - k[1] - l[1] + 1:n]; B[m - k[1] + 1:l[1], n - k[1] - l[1] + 1:n]])
1736 end
1737 U, V, Q, alpha, beta, k[1], l[1], R
1738 end
1739 end
1740 end
1741
1742 """
1743 geev!(jobvl, jobvr, A) -> (W, VL, VR)
1744
1745 Finds the eigensystem of `A`. If `jobvl = N`, the left eigenvectors of
1746 `A` aren't computed. If `jobvr = N`, the right eigenvectors of `A`
1747 aren't computed. If `jobvl = V` or `jobvr = V`, the corresponding
1748 eigenvectors are computed. Returns the eigenvalues in `W`, the right
1749 eigenvectors in `VR`, and the left eigenvectors in `VL`.
1750 """
1751 geev!(jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
1752
1753 """
1754 gesdd!(job, A) -> (U, S, VT)
1755
1756 Finds the singular value decomposition of `A`, `A = U * S * V'`,
1757 using a divide and conquer approach. If `job = A`, all the columns of `U` and
1758 the rows of `V'` are computed. If `job = N`, no columns of `U` or rows of `V'`
1759 are computed. If `job = O`, `A` is overwritten with the columns of (thin) `U`
1760 and the rows of (thin) `V'`. If `job = S`, the columns of (thin) `U` and the
1761 rows of (thin) `V'` are computed and returned separately.
1762 """
1763 gesdd!(job::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
1764
1765 """
1766 gesvd!(jobu, jobvt, A) -> (U, S, VT)
1767
1768 Finds the singular value decomposition of `A`, `A = U * S * V'`.
1769 If `jobu = A`, all the columns of `U` are computed. If `jobvt = A` all the rows
1770 of `V'` are computed. If `jobu = N`, no columns of `U` are computed. If
1771 `jobvt = N` no rows of `V'` are computed. If `jobu = O`, `A` is overwritten with
1772 the columns of (thin) `U`. If `jobvt = O`, `A` is overwritten with the rows
1773 of (thin) `V'`. If `jobu = S`, the columns of (thin) `U` are computed
1774 and returned separately. If `jobvt = S` the rows of (thin) `V'` are
1775 computed and returned separately. `jobu` and `jobvt` can't both be `O`.
1776
1777 Returns `U`, `S`, and `Vt`, where `S` are the singular values of `A`.
1778 """
1779 gesvd!(jobu::Char, jobvt::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
1780
1781 """
1782 ggsvd!(jobu, jobv, jobq, A, B) -> (U, V, Q, alpha, beta, k, l, R)
1783
1784 Finds the generalized singular value decomposition of `A` and `B`, `U'*A*Q = D1*R`
1785 and `V'*B*Q = D2*R`. `D1` has `alpha` on its diagonal and `D2` has `beta` on its
1786 diagonal. If `jobu = U`, the orthogonal/unitary matrix `U` is computed. If
1787 `jobv = V` the orthogonal/unitary matrix `V` is computed. If `jobq = Q`,
1788 the orthogonal/unitary matrix `Q` is computed. If `jobu`, `jobv` or `jobq` is
1789 `N`, that matrix is not computed. This function is only available in LAPACK
1790 versions prior to 3.6.0.
1791 """
1792 ggsvd!(jobu::Char, jobv::Char, jobq::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedMatrix)
1793

1797 @eval begin
1798 function ggsvd3!(jobu::Char, jobv::Char, jobq::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedMatrix{$elty})
1799 chkstride1(A, B)
1800 m, n = size(A)
1801 if size(B, 2) != n
1802 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has second dimension $(size(B,2)) but needs $n"))
1803 end
1804 p = size(B, 1)
1805 k = Ref{BlasInt}()
1806 l = Ref{BlasInt}()
1807 lda = max(1, stride(A, 2))
1808 ldb = max(1, stride(B, 2))
1809 alpha = similar(A, $elty, n)
1810 beta = similar(A, $elty, n)
1811 ldu = max(1, m)
1812 U = jobu == 'U' ? similar(A, $elty, ldu, m) : similar(A, $elty, 0)
1813 ldv = max(1, p)
1814 V = jobv == 'V' ? similar(A, $elty, ldv, p) : similar(A, $elty, 0)
1815 ldq = max(1, n)
1816 Q = jobq == 'Q' ? similar(A, $elty, ldq, n) : similar(A, $elty, 0)
1817 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1818 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1819 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(n)
1820 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1821 for i = 1:2
1822 ccall((@blasfunc($f), liblapack), Void,
1823 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1824 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ref{BlasInt}, Ref{BlasInt},
1825 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1826 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1827 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
1828 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ref{BlasInt}),
1829 &jobu, &jobv, &jobq, &m,
1830 &n, &p, k, l,
1831 A, &lda, B, &ldb,
1832 alpha, beta, U, &ldu,
1833 V, &ldv, Q, &ldq,
1834 work, &lwork, iwork, info)
1835 chklapackerror(info[])
1836 if i == 1
1837 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
1838 resize!(work, lwork)
1839 end
1840 end
1841 if m - k[] - l[] >= 0
1842 R = triu(A[1:k[] + l[],n - k[] - l[] + 1:n])
1843 else
1844 R = triu([A[1:m, n - k[] - l[] + 1:n]; B[m - k[] + 1:l[], n - k[] - l[] + 1:n]])
1845 end
1846 return U, V, Q, alpha, beta, k[], l[], R
1847 end
1848 end
1849 end

1891 V, &ldv, Q, &ldq,

1893 info)

1895 if i == 1

1897 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
1898 end
1899 end

1910 """
1911 ggsvd3!(jobu, jobv, jobq, A, B) -> (U, V, Q, alpha, beta, k, l, R)
1912
1913 Finds the generalized singular value decomposition of `A` and `B`, `U'*A*Q = D1*R`
1914 and `V'*B*Q = D2*R`. `D1` has `alpha` on its diagonal and `D2` has `beta` on its
1915 diagonal. If `jobu = U`, the orthogonal/unitary matrix `U` is computed. If
1916 `jobv = V` the orthogonal/unitary matrix `V` is computed. If `jobq = Q`,
1917 the orthogonal/unitary matrix `Q` is computed. If `jobu`, `jobv`, or `jobq` is
1918 `N`, that matrix is not computed. This function requires LAPACK 3.6.0.
1919 """
1920 ggsvd3!

1922 ## Expert driver and generalized eigenvalue problem
1923 for (geevx, ggev, elty) in
1924 ((:dgeevx_,:dggev_,:Float64),
1925 (:sgeevx_,:sggev_,:Float32))
1926 @eval begin
1927 # SUBROUTINE DGEEVX( BALANC, JOBVL, JOBVR, SENSE, N, A, LDA, WR, WI,
1928 # VL, LDVL, VR, LDVR, ILO, IHI, SCALE, ABNRM,
1929 # RCONDE, RCONDV, WORK, LWORK, IWORK, INFO )
1930 #
1931 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
1932 # CHARACTER BALANC, JOBVL, JOBVR, SENSE
1933 # INTEGER IHI, ILO, INFO, LDA, LDVL, LDVR, LWORK, N
1934 # DOUBLE PRECISION ABNRM
1935 # ..
1936 # .. Array Arguments ..
1937 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
1938 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), RCONDE( * ), RCONDV( * ),
1939 # $ SCALE( * ), VL( LDVL, * ), VR( LDVR, * ),
1940 # $ WI( * ), WORK( * ), WR( * )
1941 function geevx!(balanc::Char, jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, sense::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
1942 n = checksquare(A)
1943 chkfinite(A) # balancing routines don't support NaNs and Infs
1944 lda = max(1,stride(A,2))
1945 wr = similar(A, $elty, n)
1946 wi = similar(A, $elty, n)
1947 if balanc ∉ ['N', 'P', 'S', 'B']
1948 throw(ArgumentError("balanc must be 'N', 'P', 'S', or 'B', but $balanc was passed"))
1949 end
1950 ldvl = 0
1951 if jobvl == 'V'
1952 ldvl = n
1953 elseif jobvl == 'N'
1954 ldvl = 0
1955 else
1956 throw(ArgumentError("jobvl must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvl was passed"))
1957 end
1958 VL = similar(A, $elty, ldvl, n)
1959 ldvr = 0
1960 if jobvr == 'V'
1961 ldvr = n
1962 elseif jobvr == 'N'
1963 ldvr = 0
1964 else
1965 throw(ArgumentError("jobvr must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvr was passed"))
1966 end
1967 VR = similar(A, $elty, ldvr, n)
1968 ilo = Ref{BlasInt}()
1969 ihi = Ref{BlasInt}()
1970 scale = similar(A, $elty, n)
1971 abnrm = Ref{$elty}()
1972 rconde = similar(A, $elty, n)
1973 rcondv = similar(A, $elty, n)
1974 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
1975 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
1976 iworksize = 0
1977 if sense == 'N' || sense == 'E'
1978 iworksize = 0
1979 elseif sense == 'V' || sense == 'B'
1980 iworksize = 2*n - 2
1981 else
1982 throw(ArgumentError("sense must be 'N', 'E', 'V' or 'B', but $sense was passed"))
1983 end
1984 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(iworksize)
1985 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
1986 for i = 1:2
1987 ccall((@blasfunc($geevx), liblapack), Void,
1988 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8},
1989 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1990 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1991 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
1992 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
1993 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
1994 &balanc, &jobvl, &jobvr, &sense,
1995 &n, A, &lda, wr,
1996 wi, VL, &max(1,ldvl), VR,
1997 &max(1,ldvr), ilo, ihi, scale,
1998 abnrm, rconde, rcondv, work,
1999 &lwork, iwork, info)
2000 chklapackerror(info[])
2001 if i == 1
2002 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
2003 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
2004 end
2005 end
2006 A, wr, wi, VL, VR, ilo[], ihi[], scale, abnrm[], rconde, rcondv
2007 end

2009 # SUBROUTINE DGGEV( JOBVL, JOBVR, N, A, LDA, B, LDB, ALPHAR, ALPHAI,
2010 # $ BETA, VL, LDVL, VR, LDVR, WORK, LWORK, INFO )
2011 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
2012 # CHARACTER JOBVL, JOBVR
2013 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LDVL, LDVR, LWORK, N
2014 # * ..
2015 # * .. Array Arguments ..
2016 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), ALPHAI( * ), ALPHAR( * ),
2017 # $ B( LDB, * ), BETA( * ), VL( LDVL, * ),
2018 # $ VR( LDVR, * ), WORK( * )
2019 function ggev!(jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedMatrix{$elty})
2020 chkstride1(A,B)
2021 n, m = checksquare(A,B)
2022 if n != m
2023 throw(DimensionMismatch("A has dimensions $(size(A)), and B has dimensions $(size(B)), but A and B must have the same size"))
2024 end
2025 lda = max(1, stride(A, 2))
2026 ldb = max(1, stride(B, 2))
2027 alphar = similar(A, $elty, n)
2028 alphai = similar(A, $elty, n)
2029 beta = similar(A, $elty, n)
2030 ldvl = 0
2031 if jobvl == 'V'
2032 ldvl = n
2033 elseif jobvl == 'N'
2034 ldvl = 1
2035 else
2036 throw(ArgumentError("jobvl must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvl was passed"))
2037 end
2038 vl = similar(A, $elty, ldvl, n)
2039 ldvr = 0
2040 if jobvr == 'V'
2041 ldvr = n
2042 elseif jobvr == 'N'
2043 ldvr = 1
2044 else
2045 throw(ArgumentError("jobvr must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvr was passed"))
2046 end
2047 vr = similar(A, $elty, ldvr, n)
2048 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
2049 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
2050 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2051 for i = 1:2
2052 ccall((@blasfunc($ggev), liblapack), Void,
2053 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2054 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2055 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2056 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2057 Ptr{BlasInt}),
2058 &jobvl, &jobvr, &n, A,
2059 &lda, B, &ldb, alphar,
2060 alphai, beta, vl, &ldvl,
2061 vr, &ldvr, work, &lwork,
2062 info)
2063 chklapackerror(info[])
2064 if i == 1
2065 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
2066 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
2067 end
2068 end
2069 alphar, alphai, beta, vl, vr
2070 end
2071 end
2072 end

2074 for (geevx, ggev, elty, relty) in
2075 ((:zgeevx_,:zggev_,:Complex128,:Float64),
2076 (:cgeevx_,:cggev_,:Complex64,:Float32))
2077 @eval begin
2078 # SUBROUTINE ZGEEVX( BALANC, JOBVL, JOBVR, SENSE, N, A, LDA, W, VL,
2079 # LDVL, VR, LDVR, ILO, IHI, SCALE, ABNRM, RCONDE,
2080 # RCONDV, WORK, LWORK, RWORK, INFO )
2081 #
2082 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
2083 # CHARACTER BALANC, JOBVL, JOBVR, SENSE
2084 # INTEGER IHI, ILO, INFO, LDA, LDVL, LDVR, LWORK, N
2085 # DOUBLE PRECISION ABNRM
2086 # ..
2087 # .. Array Arguments ..
2088 # DOUBLE PRECISION RCONDE( * ), RCONDV( * ), RWORK( * ),
2089 # $ SCALE( * )
2090 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), VL( LDVL, * ), VR( LDVR, * ),
2091 # $ W( * ), WORK( * )
2092 function geevx!(balanc::Char, jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, sense::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
2093 n = checksquare(A)
2094 chkfinite(A) # balancing routines don't support NaNs and Infs
2095 lda = max(1,stride(A,2))
2096 w = similar(A, $elty, n)
2097 if balanc ∉ ['N', 'P', 'S', 'B']
2098 throw(ArgumentError("balanc must be 'N', 'P', 'S', or 'B', but $balanc was passed"))
2099 end
2100 ldvl = 0
2101 if jobvl == 'V'
2102 ldvl = n
2103 elseif jobvl == 'N'
2104 ldvl = 0
2105 else
2106 throw(ArgumentError("jobvl must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvl was passed"))
2107 end
2108 VL = similar(A, $elty, ldvl, n)
2109 ldvr = 0
2110 if jobvr == 'V'
2111 ldvr = n
2112 elseif jobvr == 'N'
2113 ldvr = 0
2114 else
2115 throw(ArgumentError("jobvr must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvr was passed"))
2116 end
2117 if sense ∉ ['N','E','V','B']
2118 throw(ArgumentError("sense must be 'N', 'E', 'V' or 'B', but $sense was passed"))
2119 end
2120 VR = similar(A, $elty, ldvr, n)
2121 ilo = Ref{BlasInt}()
2122 ihi = Ref{BlasInt}()
2123 scale = similar(A, $relty, n)
2124 abnrm = Ref{$relty}()
2125 rconde = similar(A, $relty, n)
2126 rcondv = similar(A, $relty, n)
2127 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
2128 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
2129 rwork = Vector{$relty}(2n)
2130 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2131 for i = 1:2
2132 ccall((@blasfunc($geevx), liblapack), Void,
2133 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8},
2134 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2135 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2136 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty},
2137 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2138 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2139 &balanc, &jobvl, &jobvr, &sense,
2140 &n, A, &lda, w,
2141 VL, &max(1,ldvl), VR, &max(1,ldvr),
2142 ilo, ihi, scale, abnrm,
2143 rconde, rcondv, work, &lwork,
2144 rwork, info)
2145 chklapackerror(info[])
2146 if i == 1
2147 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
2148 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
2149 end
2150 end
2151 A, w, VL, VR, ilo[], ihi[], scale, abnrm[], rconde, rcondv
2152 end

2154 # SUBROUTINE ZGGEV( JOBVL, JOBVR, N, A, LDA, B, LDB, ALPHA, BETA,
2155 # $ VL, LDVL, VR, LDVR, WORK, LWORK, RWORK, INFO )
2156 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
2157 # CHARACTER JOBVL, JOBVR
2158 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LDVL, LDVR, LWORK, N
2159 # * ..
2160 # * .. Array Arguments ..
2161 # DOUBLE PRECISION RWORK( * )
2162 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), ALPHA( * ), B( LDB, * ),
2163 # $ BETA( * ), VL( LDVL, * ), VR( LDVR, * ),
2164 # $ WORK( * )
2165 function ggev!(jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedMatrix{$elty})
2166 chkstride1(A, B)
2167 n, m = checksquare(A, B)
2168 if n != m
2169 throw(DimensionMismatch("A has dimensions $(size(A)), and B has dimensions $(size(B)), but A and B must have the same size"))
2170 end
2171 lda = max(1, stride(A, 2))
2172 ldb = max(1, stride(B, 2))
2173 alpha = similar(A, $elty, n)
2174 beta = similar(A, $elty, n)
2175 ldvl = 0
2176 if jobvl == 'V'
2177 ldvl = n
2178 elseif jobvl == 'N'
2179 ldvl = 1
2180 else
2181 throw(ArgumentError("jobvl must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvl was passed"))
2182 end
2183 vl = similar(A, $elty, ldvl, n)
2184 ldvr = 0
2185 if jobvr == 'V'
2186 ldvr = n
2187 elseif jobvr == 'N'
2188 ldvr = 1
2189 else
2190 throw(ArgumentError("jobvr must be 'V' or 'N', but $jobvr was passed"))
2191 end
2192 vr = similar(A, $elty, ldvr, n)
2193 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
2194 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
2195 rwork = Vector{$relty}(8n)
2196 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2197 for i = 1:2
2198 ccall((@blasfunc($ggev), liblapack), Void,
2199 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2200 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2201 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2202 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty},
2203 Ptr{BlasInt}),
2204 &jobvl, &jobvr, &n, A,
2205 &lda, B, &ldb, alpha,
2206 beta, vl, &ldvl, vr,
2207 &ldvr, work, &lwork, rwork,
2208 info)
2209 chklapackerror(info[])
2210 if i == 1
2211 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
2212 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
2213 end
2214 end
2215 alpha, beta, vl, vr
2216 end
2217 end
2218 end

2220 """
2221 geevx!(balanc, jobvl, jobvr, sense, A) -> (A, w, VL, VR, ilo, ihi, scale, abnrm, rconde, rcondv)
2222
2223 Finds the eigensystem of `A` with matrix balancing. If `jobvl = N`, the
2224 left eigenvectors of `A` aren't computed. If `jobvr = N`, the right
2225 eigenvectors of `A` aren't computed. If `jobvl = V` or `jobvr = V`, the
2226 corresponding eigenvectors are computed. If `balanc = N`, no balancing is
2227 performed. If `balanc = P`, `A` is permuted but not scaled. If
2228 `balanc = S`, `A` is scaled but not permuted. If `balanc = B`, `A` is
2229 permuted and scaled. If `sense = N`, no reciprocal condition numbers are
2230 computed. If `sense = E`, reciprocal condition numbers are computed for
2231 the eigenvalues only. If `sense = V`, reciprocal condition numbers are
2232 computed for the right eigenvectors only. If `sense = B`, reciprocal
2233 condition numbers are computed for the right eigenvectors and the
2234 eigenvectors. If `sense = E,B`, the right and left eigenvectors must be
2235 computed.
2236 """
2237 geevx!(balanc::Char, jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, sense::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
2238
2239 """
2240 ggev!(jobvl, jobvr, A, B) -> (alpha, beta, vl, vr)
2241
2242 Finds the generalized eigendecomposition of `A` and `B`. If `jobvl = N`,
2243 the left eigenvectors aren't computed. If `jobvr = N`, the right
2244 eigenvectors aren't computed. If `jobvl = V` or `jobvr = V`, the
2245 corresponding eigenvectors are computed.
2246 """
2247 ggev!(jobvl::Char, jobvr::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedMatrix)

2249 # One step incremental condition estimation of max/min singular values
2250 for (laic1, elty) in

2252 (:slaic1_,:Float32))

2254 # SUBROUTINE DLAIC1( JOB, J, X, SEST, W, GAMMA, SESTPR, S, C )
2255 #
2256 # .. Scalar Arguments ..

2258 # DOUBLE PRECISION C, GAMMA, S, SEST, SESTPR
2259 # ..
2260 # .. Array Arguments ..
2261 # DOUBLE PRECISION W( J ), X( J )
2262 function laic1!(job::Integer, x::StridedVector{$elty},
2263 sest::$elty, w::StridedVector{$elty}, gamma::$elty)
2264 j = length(x)
2265 if j != length(w)
2266 throw(DimensionMismatch("vectors must have same length, but length of x is $j and length of w is $(length(w))"))
2267 end
2268 sestpr = Vector{$elty}(1)
2269 s = Vector{$elty}(1)
2270 c = Vector{$elty}(1)
2271 ccall((@blasfunc($laic1), liblapack), Void,
2272 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
2273 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
2274 Ptr{$elty}),
2275 &job, &j, x, &sest,
2276 w, &gamma, sestpr, s,
2277 c)
2278 sestpr[1], s[1], c[1]
2279 end
2280 end
2281 end

2283 ((:zlaic1_,:Complex128,:Float64),
2284 (:claic1_,:Complex64,:Float32))

2292 # ..
2293 # .. Array Arguments ..
2294 # COMPLEX*16 W( J ), X( J )
2295 function laic1!(job::Integer, x::StridedVector{$elty},
2296 sest::$relty, w::StridedVector{$elty}, gamma::$elty)
2297 j = length(x)
2298 if j != length(w)
2299 throw(DimensionMismatch("vectors must have same length, but length of x is $j and length of w is $(length(w))"))
2300 end
2301 sestpr = Vector{$relty}(1)
2302 s = Vector{$elty}(1)

2304 ccall((@blasfunc($laic1), liblapack), Void,
2305 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$relty},
2306 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty},
2307 Ptr{$elty}),
2308 &job, &j, x, &sest,
2309 w, &gamma, sestpr, s,
2310 c)
2311 sestpr[1], s[1], c[1]
2312 end
2313 end

2316 # (GT) General tridiagonal, decomposition, solver and direct solver
2317 for (gtsv, gttrf, gttrs, elty) in
2318 ((:dgtsv_,:dgttrf_,:dgttrs_,:Float64),
2319 (:sgtsv_,:sgttrf_,:sgttrs_,:Float32),
2320 (:zgtsv_,:zgttrf_,:zgttrs_,:Complex128),
2321 (:cgtsv_,:cgttrf_,:cgttrs_,:Complex64))
2322 @eval begin
2323 # SUBROUTINE DGTSV( N, NRHS, DL, D, DU, B, LDB, INFO )
2324 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
2325 # INTEGER INFO, LDB, N, NRHS
2326 # .. Array Arguments ..
2327 # DOUBLE PRECISION B( LDB, * ), D( * ), DL( * ), DU( * )
2328 function gtsv!(dl::StridedVector{$elty}, d::StridedVector{$elty}, du::StridedVector{$elty},
2329 B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
2330 chkstride1(B, dl, d, du)
2331 n = length(d)
2332 if !(n >= length(dl) >= n - 1)
2333 throw(DimensionMismatch("subdiagonal has length $(length(dl)), but should be $n or $(n - 1)"))
2334 end
2335 if !(n >= length(du) >= n - 1)
2336 throw(DimensionMismatch("superdiagonal has length $(length(du)), but should be $n or $(n - 1)"))
2337 end
2338 if n != size(B,1)
2339 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has leading dimension $(size(B,1)), but should have $n"))
2340 end
2341 if n == 0
2342 return B # Early exit if possible
2343 end
2344 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2345 ccall((@blasfunc($gtsv), liblapack), Void,
2346 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
2347 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2348 &n, &size(B,2), dl, d, du, B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), info)
2349 chklapackerror(info[])
2350 B
2351 end
2352
2353 # SUBROUTINE DGTTRF( N, DL, D, DU, DU2, IPIV, INFO )
2354 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
2355 # INTEGER INFO, N
2356 # .. Array Arguments ..
2357 # INTEGER IPIV( * )
2358 # DOUBLE PRECISION D( * ), DL( * ), DU( * ), DU2( * )
2359 function gttrf!(dl::StridedVector{$elty}, d::StridedVector{$elty}, du::StridedVector{$elty})
2360 chkstride1(dl,d,du)
2361 n = length(d)
2362 if length(dl) != n - 1
2363 throw(DimensionMismatch("subdiagonal has length $(length(dl)), but should be $(n - 1)"))
2364 end
2365 if length(du) != n - 1
2366 throw(DimensionMismatch("superdiagonal has length $(length(du)), but should be $(n - 1)"))
2367 end
2368 du2 = similar(d, $elty, n-2)
2369 ipiv = similar(d, BlasInt, n)
2370 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2371 ccall((@blasfunc($gttrf), liblapack), Void,
2372 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
2373 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2374 &n, dl, d, du, du2, ipiv, info)
2375 chklapackerror(info[])
2376 dl, d, du, du2, ipiv
2377 end
2378
2379 # SUBROUTINE DGTTRS( TRANS, N, NRHS, DL, D, DU, DU2, IPIV, B, LDB, INFO )
2380 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
2381 # CHARACTER TRANS
2382 # INTEGER INFO, LDB, N, NRHS
2383 # .. Array Arguments ..
2384 # INTEGER IPIV( * )
2385 # DOUBLE PRECISION B( LDB, * ), D( * ), DL( * ), DU( * ), DU2( * )
2386 function gttrs!(trans::Char, dl::StridedVector{$elty}, d::StridedVector{$elty},
2387 du::StridedVector{$elty}, du2::StridedVector{$elty}, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt},
2388 B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
2389 chktrans(trans)
2390 chkstride1(B, ipiv, dl, d, du, du2)
2391 n = length(d)
2392 if length(dl) != n - 1
2393 throw(DimensionMismatch("subdiagonal has length $(length(dl)), but should be $(n - 1)"))
2394 end
2395 if length(du) != n - 1
2396 throw(DimensionMismatch("superdiagonal has length $(length(du)), but should be $(n - 1)"))
2397 end
2398 if n != size(B,1)
2399 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has leading dimension $(size(B,1)), but should have $n"))
2400 end
2401 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2402 ccall((@blasfunc($gttrs), liblapack), Void,
2403 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2404 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
2405 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2406 &trans, &n, &size(B,2), dl, d, du, du2, ipiv, B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), info)
2407 chklapackerror(info[])
2408 B
2409 end
2410 end
2411 end

2413 """
2414 gtsv!(dl, d, du, B)
2415
2416 Solves the equation `A * X = B` where `A` is a tridiagonal matrix with
2417 `dl` on the subdiagonal, `d` on the diagonal, and `du` on the
2418 superdiagonal.
2419
2420 Overwrites `B` with the solution `X` and returns it.
2421 """

2424 """
2425 gttrf!(dl, d, du) -> (dl, d, du, du2, ipiv)
2426
2427 Finds the `LU` factorization of a tridiagonal matrix with `dl` on the
2428 subdiagonal, `d` on the diagonal, and `du` on the superdiagonal.
2429
2430 Modifies `dl`, `d`, and `du` in-place and returns them and the second
2431 superdiagonal `du2` and the pivoting vector `ipiv`.
2432 """
2433 gttrf!(dl::StridedVector, d::StridedVector, du::StridedVector)
2434
2435 """
2436 gttrs!(trans, dl, d, du, du2, ipiv, B)
2437
2438 Solves the equation `A * X = B` (`trans = N`), `A.' * X = B` (`trans = T`),
2439 or `A' * X = B` (`trans = C`) using the `LU` factorization computed by
2440 `gttrf!`. `B` is overwritten with the solution `X`.
2441 """

2535 for i = 1:2
2536 ccall((@blasfunc($orgql), liblapack), Void,
2537 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
2538 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2539 &m, &n, &k, A,
2540 &max(1,stride(A,2)), tau, work, &lwork,
2541 info)
2542 chklapackerror(info[])
2543 if i == 1
2544 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
2545 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
2546 end
2547 end
2548 if n < size(A,2)
2549 A[:,1:n]
2550 else
2551 A
2552 end
2553 end

2555 # SUBROUTINE DORGRQ( M, N, K, A, LDA, TAU, WORK, LWORK, INFO )

2559 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), TAU( * ), WORK( * )
2560 function orgrq!(A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, tau::StridedVector{$elty}, k::Integer = length(tau))
2561 chkstride1(A,tau)

2613 end
2614 if side == 'R' && k > n
2615 throw(DimensionMismatch("invalid number of reflectors: k = $k should be <= n = $n"))
2616 end
2617 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
2618 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
2619 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2620 for i = 1:2

2624 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2625 &side, &trans, &m, &n, &k, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), tau,

2629 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))

2631 end

2750 throw(DimensionMismatch("for a left-sided multiplication, the first dimension of C, $m, must equal the second dimension of A, $nA"))

2779
2780 function gemqrt!(side::Char, trans::Char, V::StridedMatrix{$elty}, T::StridedMatrix{$elty}, C::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
2781 chktrans(trans)
2782 chkside(side)
2783 chkstride1(V, T, C)
2784 m,n = ndims(C) == 2 ? size(C) : (size(C, 1), 1)
2785 nb, k = size(T)
2786 if k == 0
2787 return C
2788 end
2789 if side == 'L'
2790 if !(0 <= k <= m)
2791 throw(DimensionMismatch("wrong value for k = $k: must be between 0 and $m"))
2792 end
2793 if m != size(V,1)
2794 throw(DimensionMismatch("first dimensions of C, $m, and V, $(size(V,1)) must match"))
2795 end
2796 ldv = stride(V,2)
2797 if ldv < max(1, m)
2798 throw(DimensionMismatch("Q and C don't fit! The stride of V, $ldv, is too small"))
2799 end
2800 wss = n*k
2801 elseif side == 'R'
2802 if !(0 <= k <= n)
2803 throw(DimensionMismatch("wrong value for k = $k: must be between 0 and $n"))
2804 end
2805 if n != size(V,1)
2806 throw(DimensionMismatch("second dimension of C, $n, and first dimension of V, $(size(V,1)) must match"))
2807 end
2808 ldv = stride(V,2)
2809 if ldv < max(1, n)
2810 throw(DimensionMismatch("Q and C don't fit! The stride of V, $ldv, is too small"))
2811 end
2812 wss = m*k
2813 end
2814 if !(1 <= nb <= k)
2815 throw(DimensionMismatch("wrong value for nb = $nb, which must be between 1 and $k"))
2816 end
2817 ldc = stride(C, 2)
2818 work = Vector{$elty}(wss)
2819 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2820 ccall((@blasfunc($gemqrt), liblapack), Void,
2821 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2822 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2823 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2824 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2825 &side, &trans, &m, &n,
2826 &k, &nb, V, &ldv,
2827 T, &max(1,stride(T,2)), C, &max(1,ldc),
2828 work, info)
2829 chklapackerror(info[])
2830 return C
2831 end
2832 end
2833 end
2834
2835 """
2836 orglq!(A, tau, k = length(tau))
2837
2838 Explicitly finds the matrix `Q` of a `LQ` factorization after calling
2839 `gelqf!` on `A`. Uses the output of `gelqf!`. `A` is overwritten by `Q`.
2840 """
2841 orglq!(A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, k::Integer = length(tau))
2842
2843 """
2844 orgqr!(A, tau, k = length(tau))
2845
2846 Explicitly finds the matrix `Q` of a `QR` factorization after calling
2847 `geqrf!` on `A`. Uses the output of `geqrf!`. `A` is overwritten by `Q`.
2848 """
2849 orgqr!(A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, k::Integer = length(tau))
2850
2851 """
2852 orgql!(A, tau, k = length(tau))
2853
2854 Explicitly finds the matrix `Q` of a `QL` factorization after calling
2855 `geqlf!` on `A`. Uses the output of `geqlf!`. `A` is overwritten by `Q`.
2856 """
2857 orgql!(A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, k::Integer = length(tau))
2858
2859 """
2860 orgrq!(A, tau, k = length(tau))
2861
2862 Explicitly finds the matrix `Q` of a `RQ` factorization after calling
2863 `gerqf!` on `A`. Uses the output of `gerqf!`. `A` is overwritten by `Q`.
2864 """
2865 orgrq!(A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, k::Integer = length(tau))
2866
2867 """
2868 ormlq!(side, trans, A, tau, C)
2869
2870 Computes `Q * C` (`trans = N`), `Q.' * C` (`trans = T`), `Q' * C`
2871 (`trans = C`) for `side = L` or the equivalent right-sided multiplication
2872 for `side = R` using `Q` from a `LQ` factorization of `A` computed using
2873 `gelqf!`. `C` is overwritten.
2874 """
2875 ormlq!(side::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, C::StridedVecOrMat)
2876
2877 """
2878 ormqr!(side, trans, A, tau, C)
2879
2880 Computes `Q * C` (`trans = N`), `Q.' * C` (`trans = T`), `Q' * C`
2881 (`trans = C`) for `side = L` or the equivalent right-sided multiplication
2882 for `side = R` using `Q` from a `QR` factorization of `A` computed using
2883 `geqrf!`. `C` is overwritten.
2884 """
2885 ormqr!(side::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, C::StridedVecOrMat)
2886
2887 """
2888 ormql!(side, trans, A, tau, C)
2889
2890 Computes `Q * C` (`trans = N`), `Q.' * C` (`trans = T`), `Q' * C`
2891 (`trans = C`) for `side = L` or the equivalent right-sided multiplication
2892 for `side = R` using `Q` from a `QL` factorization of `A` computed using
2893 `geqlf!`. `C` is overwritten.
2894 """
2895 ormql!(side::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, C::StridedVecOrMat)
2896
2897 """
2898 ormrq!(side, trans, A, tau, C)
2899
2900 Computes `Q * C` (`trans = N`), `Q.' * C` (`trans = T`), `Q' * C`
2901 (`trans = C`) for `side = L` or the equivalent right-sided multiplication
2902 for `side = R` using `Q` from a `RQ` factorization of `A` computed using
2903 `gerqf!`. `C` is overwritten.
2904 """
2905 ormrq!(side::Char, trans::Char, A::StridedMatrix, tau::StridedVector, C::StridedVecOrMat)
2906
2907 """
2908 gemqrt!(side, trans, V, T, C)
2909
2910 Computes `Q * C` (`trans = N`), `Q.' * C` (`trans = T`), `Q' * C`
2911 (`trans = C`) for `side = L` or the equivalent right-sided multiplication
2912 for `side = R` using `Q` from a `QR` factorization of `A` computed using
2913 `geqrt!`. `C` is overwritten.
2914 """
2915 gemqrt!(side::Char, trans::Char, V::StridedMatrix, T::StridedMatrix, C::StridedVecOrMat)
2916
2917 # (PO) positive-definite symmetric matrices,
2918 for (posv, potrf, potri, potrs, pstrf, elty, rtyp) in
2919 ((:dposv_,:dpotrf_,:dpotri_,:dpotrs_,:dpstrf_,:Float64,:Float64),
2920 (:sposv_,:spotrf_,:spotri_,:spotrs_,:spstrf_,:Float32,:Float32),
2921 (:zposv_,:zpotrf_,:zpotri_,:zpotrs_,:zpstrf_,:Complex128,:Float64),
2922 (:cposv_,:cpotrf_,:cpotri_,:cpotrs_,:cpstrf_,:Complex64,:Float32))
2923 @eval begin
2924 # SUBROUTINE DPOSV( UPLO, N, NRHS, A, LDA, B, LDB, INFO )
2925 #* .. Scalar Arguments ..
2926 # CHARACTER UPLO
2927 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, N, NRHS
2928 # .. Array Arguments ..
2929 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * )
2930 function posv!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
2931 chkstride1(A, B)
2932 n = checksquare(A)
2933 chkuplo(uplo)
2934 if size(B,1) != n
2935 throw(DimensionMismatch("first dimension of B, $(size(B,1)), and size of A, ($n,$n), must match!"))
2936 end
2937 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2938 ccall((@blasfunc($posv), liblapack), Void,
2939 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
2940 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2941 &uplo, &n, &size(B,2), A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), info)
2942 chkargsok(info[])
2943 chkposdef(info[])
2944 A, B
2945 end
2946
2947 # SUBROUTINE DPOTRF( UPLO, N, A, LDA, INFO )
2948 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
2949 # CHARACTER UPLO
2950 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, N
2951 # * .. Array Arguments ..
2952 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * )
2953 function potrf!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
2954 chkstride1(A)
2955 checksquare(A)
2956 chkuplo(uplo)
2957 lda = max(1,stride(A,2))
2958 if lda == 0
2959 return A, 0
2960 end
2961 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2962 ccall((@blasfunc($potrf), liblapack), Void,
2963 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2964 &uplo, &size(A,1), A, &lda, info)
2965 chkargsok(info[])
2966 #info[1]>0 means the leading minor of order info[i] is not positive definite
2967 #ordinarily, throw Exception here, but return error code here
2968 #this simplifies isposdef! and factorize
2969 return A, info[]
2970 end
2971
2972 # SUBROUTINE DPOTRI( UPLO, N, A, LDA, INFO )
2973 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
2974 # CHARACTER UPLO
2975 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, N
2976 # .. Array Arguments ..
2977 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * )
2978 function potri!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
2979 chkstride1(A)
2980 chkuplo(uplo)
2981 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
2982 ccall((@blasfunc($potri), liblapack), Void,
2983 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
2984 &uplo, &size(A,1), A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), info)
2985 chkargsok(info[])
2986 chknonsingular(info[])
2987 A
2988 end
2989
2990 # SUBROUTINE DPOTRS( UPLO, N, NRHS, A, LDA, B, LDB, INFO )
2991 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
2992 # CHARACTER UPLO
2993 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, N, NRHS
2994 # .. Array Arguments ..
2995 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * )
2996 function potrs!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
2997 chkstride1(A, B)
2998 n = checksquare(A)
2999 chkuplo(uplo)
3000 nrhs = size(B,2)
3001 if size(B,1) != n
3002 throw(DimensionMismatch("first dimension of B, $(size(B,1)), and size of A, ($n,$n), must match!"))
3003 end
3004 lda = max(1,stride(A,2))
3005 if lda == 0 || nrhs == 0
3006 return B
3007 end
3008 ldb = max(1,stride(B,2))
3009 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3010 ccall((@blasfunc($potrs), liblapack), Void,
3011 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3012 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
3013 &uplo, &n, &nrhs, A,
3014 &lda, B, &ldb, info)
3015 chklapackerror(info[])
3016 return B
3017 end
3018
3019 # SUBROUTINE DPSTRF( UPLO, N, A, LDA, PIV, RANK, TOL, WORK, INFO )
3020 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
3021 # DOUBLE PRECISION TOL
3022 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, N, RANK
3023 # CHARACTER UPLO
3024 # .. Array Arguments ..
3025 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), WORK( 2*N )
3026 # INTEGER PIV( N )
3027 function pstrf!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, tol::Real)
3028 chkstride1(A)
3029 n = checksquare(A)
3030 chkuplo(uplo)
3031 piv = similar(A, BlasInt, n)
3032 rank = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
3033 work = Vector{$rtyp}(2n)
3034 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3035 ccall((@blasfunc($pstrf), liblapack), Void,
3036 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3037 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$rtyp}, Ptr{$rtyp}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
