3544 # .. Array Arguments ..
3545 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
3546 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), BERR( * ), FERR( * ),
3547 #$ WORK( * ), X( LDX, * )
3548 function trrfs!(uplo::Char, trans::Char, diag::Char,
3549 A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty}, X::StridedVecOrMat{$elty},
3550 Ferr::StridedVector{$relty} = similar(B, $relty, size(B,2)),
3551 Berr::StridedVector{$relty} = similar(B, $relty, size(B,2)))
3552 chktrans(trans)
3553 chkuplo(uplo)
3554 chkdiag(diag)
3555 n = size(A,2)
3556 nrhs = size(B,2)
3557 if nrhs != size(X,2)
3558 throw(DimensionMismatch("second dimensions of B, $nrhs, and X, $(size(X,2)), must match"))
3559 end
3560 work = Vector{$elty}(2n)
3561 rwork = Vector{$relty}(n)
3562 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3563 ccall((@blasfunc($trrfs), liblapack), Void,
3564 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3565 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3566 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
3567 &uplo, &trans, &diag, &n,
3568 &nrhs, A, &max(1,stride(A,2)), B, &max(1,stride(B,2)), X, &max(1,stride(X,2)),
3569 Ferr, Berr, work, rwork, info)
3570 chklapackerror(info[])
3571 Ferr, Berr
3572 end
3573 end
3574 end
3575
3576 """
3577 trcon!(norm, uplo, diag, A)
3578
3579 Finds the reciprocal condition number of (upper if `uplo = U`, lower if
3580 `uplo = L`) triangular matrix `A`. If `diag = N`, `A` has non-unit
3581 diagonal elements. If `diag = U`, all diagonal elements of `A` are one.
3582 If `norm = I`, the condition number is found in the infinity norm. If
3583 `norm = O` or `1`, the condition number is found in the one norm.
3584 """
3585 trcon!(norm::Char, uplo::Char, diag::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
3586
3587 """
3588 trevc!(side, howmny, select, T, VL = similar(T), VR = similar(T))
3589
3590 Finds the eigensystem of an upper triangular matrix `T`. If `side = R`,
3591 the right eigenvectors are computed. If `side = L`, the left
3592 eigenvectors are computed. If `side = B`, both sets are computed. If
3593 `howmny = A`, all eigenvectors are found. If `howmny = B`, all
3594 eigenvectors are found and backtransformed using `VL` and `VR`. If
3595 `howmny = S`, only the eigenvectors corresponding to the values in
3596 `select` are computed.
3597 """
3598 trevc!(side::Char, howmny::Char, select::StridedVector{BlasInt}, T::StridedMatrix,
3599 VL::StridedMatrix = similar(T), VR::StridedMatrix = similar(T))
3600
3601 """
3602 trrfs!(uplo, trans, diag, A, B, X, Ferr, Berr) -> (Ferr, Berr)
3603
3604 Estimates the error in the solution to `A * X = B` (`trans = N`),
3605 `A.' * X = B` (`trans = T`), `A' * X = B` (`trans = C`) for `side = L`,
3606 or the equivalent equations a right-handed `side = R` `X * A` after
3607 computing `X` using `trtrs!`. If `uplo = U`, `A` is upper triangular.
3608 If `uplo = L`, `A` is lower triangular. If `diag = N`, `A` has non-unit
3609 diagonal elements. If `diag = U`, all diagonal elements of `A` are one.
3610 `Ferr` and `Berr` are optional inputs. `Ferr` is the forward error and
3611 `Berr` is the backward error, each component-wise.
3612 """
3613 trrfs!(uplo::Char, trans::Char, diag::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat,
3614 X::StridedVecOrMat, Ferr::StridedVector, Berr::StridedVector)
3615
3616 ## (ST) Symmetric tridiagonal - eigendecomposition
3617 for (stev, stebz, stegr, stein, elty) in
3618 ((:dstev_,:dstebz_,:dstegr_,:dstein_,:Float64),
3619 (:sstev_,:sstebz_,:sstegr_,:sstein_,:Float32)
3620 # , (:zstev_,:Complex128) Need to rewrite for ZHEEV, rwork, etc.
3621 # , (:cstev_,:Complex64)
3622 )
3623 @eval begin
3624 function stev!(job::Char, dv::StridedVector{$elty}, ev::StridedVector{$elty})
3625 chkstride1(dv, ev)
3626 n = length(dv)
3627 if length(ev) != n - 1
3628 throw(DimensionMismatch("ev has length $(length(ev)) but needs one less than dv's length, $n)"))
3629 end
3630 Zmat = similar(dv, $elty, (n, job != 'N' ? n : 0))
3631 work = Vector{$elty}(max(1, 2n-2))
3632 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3633 ccall((@blasfunc($stev), liblapack), Void,
3634 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
3635 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
3636 &job, &n, dv, ev, Zmat, &n, work, info)
3637 chklapackerror(info[])
3638 dv, Zmat
3639 end
3640
3641 #* DSTEBZ computes the eigenvalues of a symmetric tridiagonal
3642 #* matrix T. The user may ask for all eigenvalues, all eigenvalues
3643 #* in the half-open interval (VL, VU], or the IL-th through IU-th
3644 #* eigenvalues.
3645 function stebz!(range::Char, order::Char, vl::$elty, vu::$elty, il::Integer, iu::Integer, abstol::Real, dv::StridedVector{$elty}, ev::StridedVector{$elty})
3646 chkstride1(dv, ev)
3647 n = length(dv)
3648 if length(ev) != n - 1
3649 throw(DimensionMismatch("ev has length $(length(ev)) but needs one less than dv's length, $n)"))
3650 end
3651 m = Ref{BlasInt}()
3652 nsplit = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
3653 w = similar(dv, $elty, n)
3654 tmp = 0.0
3655 iblock = similar(dv, BlasInt,n)
3656 isplit = similar(dv, BlasInt,n)
3657 work = Vector{$elty}(4*n)
3658 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(3*n)
3659 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3660 ccall((@blasfunc($stebz), liblapack), Void,
3661 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3662 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3663 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3664 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3665 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
3666 &range, &order, &n, &vl,
3667 &vu, &il, &iu, &abstol,
3668 dv, ev, m, nsplit,
3669 w, iblock, isplit, work,
3670 iwork, info)
3671 chklapackerror(info[])
3672 w[1:m[]], iblock[1:m[]], isplit[1:nsplit[1]]
3673 end
3674
3675 function stegr!(jobz::Char, range::Char, dv::StridedVector{$elty}, ev::StridedVector{$elty}, vl::Real, vu::Real, il::Integer, iu::Integer)
3676 chkstride1(dv, ev)
3677 n = length(dv)
3678 if length(ev) != n - 1
3679 throw(DimensionMismatch("ev has length $(length(ev)) but needs one less than dv's length, $n)"))
3680 end
3681 eev = [ev; zero($elty)]
3682 abstol = Vector{$elty}(1)
3683 m = Ref{BlasInt}()
3684 w = similar(dv, $elty, n)
3685 ldz = jobz == 'N' ? 1 : n
3686 Z = similar(dv, $elty, ldz, range == 'I' ? iu-il+1 : n)
3687 isuppz = similar(dv, BlasInt, 2*size(Z, 2))
3688 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
3689 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
3690 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
3691 liwork = BlasInt(-1)
3692 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3693 for i = 1:2
3694 ccall((@blasfunc($stegr), liblapack), Void,
3695 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3696 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3697 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3698 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3699 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
3700 &jobz, &range, &n, dv,
3701 eev, &vl, &vu, &il,
3702 &iu, abstol, m, w,
3703 Z, &ldz, isuppz, work,
3704 &lwork, iwork, &liwork, info)
3705 chklapackerror(info[])
3706 if i == 1
3707 lwork = BlasInt(work[1])
3708 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
3709 liwork = iwork[1]
3710 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(liwork)
3711 end
3712 end
3713 m[] == length(w) ? w : w[1:m[]], m[] == size(Z, 2) ? Z : Z[:,1:m[]]
3714 end
3715
3716 function stein!(dv::StridedVector{$elty}, ev_in::StridedVector{$elty}, w_in::StridedVector{$elty}, iblock_in::StridedVector{BlasInt}, isplit_in::StridedVector{BlasInt})
3717 chkstride1(dv, ev_in, w_in, iblock_in, isplit_in)
3718 n = length(dv)
3719 if length(ev_in) != n - 1
3720 throw(DimensionMismatch("ev_in has length $(length(ev_in)) but needs one less than dv's length, $n)"))
3721 end
3722 ev = [ev_in; zeros($elty,1)]
3723 ldz = n #Leading dimension
3724 #Number of eigenvalues to find
3725 if !(1 <= length(w_in) <= n)
3726 throw(DimensionMismatch("w_in has length $(length(w_in)), but needs to be between 1 and $n"))
3727 end
3728 m = length(w_in)
3729 #If iblock and isplit are invalid input, assume worst-case block paritioning,
3730 # i.e. set the block scheme to be the entire matrix
3731 iblock = similar(dv, BlasInt,n)
3732 isplit = similar(dv, BlasInt,n)
3733 w = similar(dv, $elty,n)
3734 if length(iblock_in) < m #Not enough block specifications
3735 iblock[1:m] = ones(BlasInt, m)
3736 w[1:m] = sort(w_in)
3737 else
3738 iblock[1:m] = iblock_in
3739 w[1:m] = w_in #Assume user has sorted the eigenvalues properly
3740 end
3741 if length(isplit_in) < 1 #Not enough block specifications
3742 isplit[1] = n
3743 else
3744 isplit[1:length(isplit_in)] = isplit_in
3745 end
3746 z = similar(dv, $elty,(n,m))
3747 work = Vector{$elty}(5*n)
3748 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(n)
3749 ifail = Vector{BlasInt}(m)
3750 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3751 ccall((@blasfunc($stein), liblapack), Void,
3752 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3753 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
3754 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3755 Ptr{BlasInt}),
3756 &n, dv, ev, &m, w, iblock, isplit, z, &ldz, work, iwork, ifail, info)
3757 chklapackerror(info[])
3758 if any(ifail .!= 0)
3759 # TODO: better error message / type
3760 error("failed to converge eigenvectors:\n$(nonzeros(ifail))")
3761 end
3762 z
3763 end
3764 end
3765 end
3766 stegr!(jobz::Char, dv::StridedVector, ev::StridedVector) = stegr!(jobz, 'A', dv, ev, 0.0, 0.0, 0, 0)
3767
3768 # Allow user to skip specification of iblock and isplit
3769 stein!(dv::StridedVector, ev::StridedVector, w_in::StridedVector)=stein!(dv, ev, w_in, zeros(BlasInt,0), zeros(BlasInt,0))
3770 # Allow user to specify just one eigenvector to get in stein!
3771 stein!(dv::StridedVector, ev::StridedVector, eval::Real)=stein!(dv, ev, [eval], zeros(BlasInt,0), zeros(BlasInt,0))
3772
3773 """
3774 stev!(job, dv, ev) -> (dv, Zmat)
3775
3776 Computes the eigensystem for a symmetric tridiagonal matrix with `dv` as
3777 diagonal and `ev` as off-diagonal. If `job = N` only the eigenvalues are
3778 found and returned in `dv`. If `job = V` then the eigenvectors are also found
3779 and returned in `Zmat`.
3780 """
3781 stev!(job::Char, dv::StridedVector, ev::StridedVector)
3782
3783 """
3784 stebz!(range, order, vl, vu, il, iu, abstol, dv, ev) -> (dv, iblock, isplit)
3785
3786 Computes the eigenvalues for a symmetric tridiagonal matrix with `dv` as
3787 diagonal and `ev` as off-diagonal. If `range = A`, all the eigenvalues
3788 are found. If `range = V`, the eigenvalues in the half-open interval
3789 `(vl, vu]` are found. If `range = I`, the eigenvalues with indices between
3790 `il` and `iu` are found. If `order = B`, eigvalues are ordered within a
3791 block. If `order = E`, they are ordered across all the blocks.
3792 `abstol` can be set as a tolerance for convergence.
3793 """
3794 stebz!(range::Char, order::Char, vl, vu, il::Integer, iu::Integer, abstol::Real, dv::StridedVector, ev::StridedVector)
3795
3796 """
3797 stegr!(jobz, range, dv, ev, vl, vu, il, iu) -> (w, Z)
3798
3799 Computes the eigenvalues (`jobz = N`) or eigenvalues and eigenvectors
3800 (`jobz = V`) for a symmetric tridiagonal matrix with `dv` as diagonal
3801 and `ev` as off-diagonal. If `range = A`, all the eigenvalues
3802 are found. If `range = V`, the eigenvalues in the half-open interval
3803 `(vl, vu]` are found. If `range = I`, the eigenvalues with indices between
3804 `il` and `iu` are found. The eigenvalues are returned in `w` and the eigenvectors
3805 in `Z`.
3806 """
3807 stegr!(jobz::Char, range::Char, dv::StridedVector, ev::StridedVector, vl::Real, vu::Real, il::Integer, iu::Integer)
3808
3809 """
3810 stein!(dv, ev_in, w_in, iblock_in, isplit_in)
3811
3812 Computes the eigenvectors for a symmetric tridiagonal matrix with `dv`
3813 as diagonal and `ev_in` as off-diagonal. `w_in` specifies the input
3814 eigenvalues for which to find corresponding eigenvectors. `iblock_in`
3815 specifies the submatrices corresponding to the eigenvalues in `w_in`.
3816 `isplit_in` specifies the splitting points between the submatrix blocks.
3817 """

3850 # CHARACTER UPLO

3855 function sysv!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
3856 chkstride1(A,B)

3859 if n != size(B,1)
3860 throw(DimensionMismatch("B has first dimension $(size(B,1)), but needs $n"))

3868 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},

3872 chkargsok(info[])
3873 chknonsingular(info[])
3874 if i == 1
3875 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
3876 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
3877 end
3878 end
3879 B, A, ipiv
3880 end

3882 # SUBROUTINE DSYTRF( UPLO, N, A, LDA, IPIV, WORK, LWORK, INFO )

3892 chkuplo(uplo)
3893 ipiv = similar(A, BlasInt, n)
3894 if n == 0
3895 return A, ipiv
3896 end
3897 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
3898 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
3899 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
3900 for i = 1:2
3901 ccall((@blasfunc($sytrf), liblapack), Void,
3902 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
3903 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
3904 &uplo, &n, A, &stride(A,2), ipiv, work, &lwork, info)
3905 chkargsok(info[])
3906 if i == 1
3907 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
3908 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
3909 end
3910 end
3911 return A, ipiv, info[]
3912 end

3992 # Rook-pivoting variants of symmetric-matrix algorithms
3993 for (sysv, sytrf, sytri, sytrs, elty) in
3994 ((:dsysv_rook_,:dsytrf_rook_,:dsytri_rook_,:dsytrs_rook_,:Float64),
3995 (:ssysv_rook_,:ssytrf_rook_,:ssytri_rook_,:ssytrs_rook_,:Float32))
3996 @eval begin
3997 # SUBROUTINE DSYSV_ROOK(UPLO, N, NRHS, A, LDA, IPIV, B, LDB, WORK,
3998 # LWORK, INFO )
3999 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
4000 # CHARACTER UPLO
4001 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LWORK, N, NRHS
4002 # .. Array Arguments ..
4003 # INTEGER IPIV( * )
4004 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), WORK( * )
4005 function sysv_rook!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})
4006 chkstride1(A,B)
4007 n = checksquare(A)
4008 chkuplo(uplo)
4009 if n != size(B,1)

4673 """
4674 syconv!(uplo, A, ipiv) -> (A, work)
4675
4676 Converts a symmetric matrix `A` (which has been factorized into a
4677 triangular matrix) into two matrices `L` and `D`. If `uplo = U`, `A`
4678 is upper triangular. If `uplo = L`, it is lower triangular. `ipiv` is
4679 the pivot vector from the triangular factorization. `A` is overwritten
4680 by `L` and `D`.
4681 """
4682 syconv!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt})
4683
4684 """
4685 sysv!(uplo, A, B) -> (B, A, ipiv)
4686
4687 Finds the solution to `A * X = B` for symmetric matrix `A`. If `uplo = U`,
4688 the upper half of `A` is stored. If `uplo = L`, the lower half is stored.
4689 `B` is overwritten by the solution `X`. `A` is overwritten by its
4690 Bunch-Kaufman factorization. `ipiv` contains pivoting information about the
4691 factorization.
4692 """
4693 sysv!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat)
4694
4695 """
4696 sytrf!(uplo, A) -> (A, ipiv, info)
4697
4698 Computes the Bunch-Kaufman factorization of a symmetric matrix `A`. If
4699 `uplo = U`, the upper half of `A` is stored. If `uplo = L`, the lower
4700 half is stored.
4701
4702 Returns `A`, overwritten by the factorization, a pivot vector `ipiv`, and
4703 the error code `info` which is a non-negative integer. If `info` is positive
4704 the matrix is singular and the diagonal part of the factorization is exactly
4705 zero at position `info`.
4706 """
4707 sytrf!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
4708
4709 """
4710 sytri!(uplo, A, ipiv)
4711
4712 Computes the inverse of a symmetric matrix `A` using the results of
4713 `sytrf!`. If `uplo = U`, the upper half of `A` is stored. If `uplo = L`,
4714 the lower half is stored. `A` is overwritten by its inverse.
4715 """
4716 sytri!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt})
4717
4718 """
4719 sytrs!(uplo, A, ipiv, B)
4720
4721 Solves the equation `A * X = B` for a symmetric matrix `A` using the
4722 results of `sytrf!`. If `uplo = U`, the upper half of `A` is stored.
4723 If `uplo = L`, the lower half is stored. `B` is overwritten by the
4724 solution `X`.
4725 """
4726 sytrs!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt}, B::StridedVecOrMat)
4727
4728
4729 """
4730 hesv!(uplo, A, B) -> (B, A, ipiv)
4731
4732 Finds the solution to `A * X = B` for Hermitian matrix `A`. If `uplo = U`,
4733 the upper half of `A` is stored. If `uplo = L`, the lower half is stored.
4734 `B` is overwritten by the solution `X`. `A` is overwritten by its
4735 Bunch-Kaufman factorization. `ipiv` contains pivoting information about the
4736 factorization.
4737 """
4738 hesv!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedVecOrMat)
4739
4740 """
4741 hetrf!(uplo, A) -> (A, ipiv, info)
4742
4743 Computes the Bunch-Kaufman factorization of a Hermitian matrix `A`. If
4744 `uplo = U`, the upper half of `A` is stored. If `uplo = L`, the lower
4745 half is stored.
4746
4747 Returns `A`, overwritten by the factorization, a pivot vector `ipiv`, and
4748 the error code `info` which is a non-negative integer. If `info` is positive
4749 the matrix is singular and the diagonal part of the factorization is exactly
4750 zero at position `info`.
4751 """
4752 hetrf!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
4753
4754 """
4755 hetri!(uplo, A, ipiv)
4756
4757 Computes the inverse of a Hermitian matrix `A` using the results of
4758 `sytrf!`. If `uplo = U`, the upper half of `A` is stored. If `uplo = L`,
4759 the lower half is stored. `A` is overwritten by its inverse.
4760 """
4761 hetri!(uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, ipiv::StridedVector{BlasInt})

4763 """
4764 hetrs!(uplo, A, ipiv, B)

4800 end
4801 end
4802 jobz == 'V' ? (W, A) : W
4803 end

4805 # SUBROUTINE DSYEVR( JOBZ, RANGE, UPLO, N, A, LDA, VL, VU, IL, IU,

4809 # CHARACTER JOBZ, RANGE, UPLO

4815 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), W( * ), WORK( * ), Z( LDZ, * )
4816 function syevr!(jobz::Char, range::Char, uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty},
4817 vl::AbstractFloat, vu::AbstractFloat, il::Integer, iu::Integer, abstol::AbstractFloat)
4818 chkstride1(A)
4819 n = checksquare(A)
4820 if range == 'I' && !(1 <= il <= iu <= n)
4821 throw(ArgumentError("illegal choice of eigenvalue indices (il = $il, iu = $iu), which must be between 1 and n = $n"))
4822 end
4823 if range == 'V' && vl >= vu
4824 throw(ArgumentError("lower boundary, $vl, must be less than upper boundary, $vu"))
4825 end
4826 lda = stride(A,2)
4827 m = Ref{BlasInt}()
4828 w = similar(A, $elty, n)
4829 ldz = n
4830 if jobz == 'N'
4831 Z = similar(A, $elty, ldz, 0)
4832 elseif jobz == 'V'
4833 Z = similar(A, $elty, ldz, n)
4834 end
4835 isuppz = similar(A, BlasInt, 2*n)
4836 work = Vector{$elty}(1)

4843 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt},

4845 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
4846 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
4847 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
4848 Ptr{BlasInt}),
4849 &jobz, &range, &uplo, &n,
4850 A, &max(1,lda), &vl, &vu,
4851 &il, &iu, &abstol, m,
4852 w, Z, &max(1,ldz), isuppz,
4853 work, &lwork, iwork, &liwork,
4854 info)
4855 chklapackerror(info[])
4856 if i == 1
4857 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
4858 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
4859 liwork = iwork[1]
4860 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(liwork)
4861 end
4862 end
4863 w[1:m[]], Z[:,1:(jobz == 'V' ? m[] : 0)]
4864 end
4865 syevr!(jobz::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}) =
4866 syevr!(jobz, 'A', 'U', A, 0.0, 0.0, 0, 0, -1.0)

5005 chklapackerror(info[])
5006 if i == 1
5007 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5008 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5009 lrwork = BlasInt(rwork[1])
5010 rwork = Vector{$relty}(lrwork)
5011 liwork = iwork[1]
5012 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(liwork)
5013 end
5014 end
5015 w[1:m[]], Z[:,1:(jobz == 'V' ? m[] : 0)]
5016 end
5017 syevr!(jobz::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}) =
5018 syevr!(jobz, 'A', 'U', A, 0.0, 0.0, 0, 0, -1.0)
5019
5020 # SUBROUTINE ZHEGVD( ITYPE, JOBZ, UPLO, N, A, LDA, B, LDB, W, WORK,
5021 # $ LWORK, RWORK, LRWORK, IWORK, LIWORK, INFO )
5022 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
5023 # CHARACTER JOBZ, UPLO
5024 # INTEGER INFO, ITYPE, LDA, LDB, LIWORK, LRWORK, LWORK, N
5025 # * ..
5026 # * .. Array Arguments ..
5027 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
5028 # DOUBLE PRECISION RWORK( * ), W( * )
5029 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), B( LDB, * ), WORK( * )
5030 function sygvd!(itype::Integer, jobz::Char, uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedMatrix{$elty})
5031 chkstride1(A, B)
5032 n, m = checksquare(A, B)
5033 if n != m
5034 throw(DimensionMismatch("dimensions of A, ($n,$n), and B, ($m,$m), must match"))
5035 end
5036 lda = max(1, stride(A, 2))
5037 ldb = max(1, stride(B, 2))
5038 w = similar(A, $relty, n)
5039 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
5040 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
5041 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
5042 liwork = BlasInt(-1)
5043 rwork = Array{$relty,0}()
5044 lrwork = BlasInt(-1)
5045 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
5046 for i = 1:2
5047 ccall((@blasfunc($sygvd), liblapack), Void,
5048 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5049 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5050 Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty},
5051 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
5052 &itype, &jobz, &uplo, &n,
5053 A, &lda, B, &ldb,
5054 w, work, &lwork, rwork,
5055 &lrwork, iwork, &liwork, info)
5056 chkargsok(info[])
5057 if i == 1
5058 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5059 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5060 liwork = iwork[1]
5061 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(liwork)
5062 lrwork = BlasInt(rwork[1])
5063 rwork = Vector{$relty}(lrwork)
5064 end
5065 end
5066 chkposdef(info[])
5067 w, A, B
5068 end
5069 end
5070 end

5072 """
5073 syev!(jobz, uplo, A)
5074
5075 Finds the eigenvalues (`jobz = N`) or eigenvalues and eigenvectors
5076 (`jobz = V`) of a symmetric matrix `A`. If `uplo = U`, the upper triangle
5077 of `A` is used. If `uplo = L`, the lower triangle of `A` is used.
5078 """
5079 syev!(jobz::Char, uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix)
5080
5081 """
5082 syevr!(jobz, range, uplo, A, vl, vu, il, iu, abstol) -> (W, Z)
5083
5084 Finds the eigenvalues (`jobz = N`) or eigenvalues and eigenvectors
5085 (`jobz = V`) of a symmetric matrix `A`. If `uplo = U`, the upper triangle
5086 of `A` is used. If `uplo = L`, the lower triangle of `A` is used. If
5087 `range = A`, all the eigenvalues are found. If `range = V`, the
5088 eigenvalues in the half-open interval `(vl, vu]` are found.
5089 If `range = I`, the eigenvalues with indices between `il` and `iu` are
5090 found. `abstol` can be set as a tolerance for convergence.
5091
5092 The eigenvalues are returned in `W` and the eigenvectors in `Z`.
5093 """
5094 syevr!(jobz::Char, range::Char, uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix,
5095 vl::AbstractFloat, vu::AbstractFloat, il::Integer, iu::Integer, abstol::AbstractFloat)
5096
5097 """
5098 sygvd!(itype, jobz, uplo, A, B) -> (w, A, B)
5099
5100 Finds the generalized eigenvalues (`jobz = N`) or eigenvalues and
5101 eigenvectors (`jobz = V`) of a symmetric matrix `A` and symmetric
5102 positive-definite matrix `B`. If `uplo = U`, the upper triangles
5103 of `A` and `B` are used. If `uplo = L`, the lower triangles of `A` and
5104 `B` are used. If `itype = 1`, the problem to solve is
5105 `A * x = lambda * B * x`. If `itype = 2`, the problem to solve is
5106 `A * B * x = lambda * x`. If `itype = 3`, the problem to solve is
5107 `B * A * x = lambda * x`.
5108 """
5109 sygvd!(itype::Integer, jobz::Char, uplo::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedMatrix)
5110
5111 ## (BD) Bidiagonal matrices - singular value decomposition
5112 for (bdsqr, relty, elty) in
5113 ((:dbdsqr_,:Float64,:Float64),
5114 (:sbdsqr_,:Float32,:Float32),
5115 (:zbdsqr_,:Float64,:Complex128),
5116 (:cbdsqr_,:Float32,:Complex64))
5117 @eval begin
5118 function bdsqr!(uplo::Char, d::StridedVector{$relty}, e_::StridedVector{$relty},
5119 Vt::StridedMatrix{$elty}, U::StridedMatrix{$elty}, C::StridedMatrix{$elty})
5120 chkstride1(d, e_)
5121 # Extract number
5122 n = length(d)
5123 ncvt, nru, ncc = size(Vt, 2), size(U, 1), size(C, 2)
5124 ldvt, ldu, ldc = max(1, stride(Vt,2)), max(1, stride(U, 2)), max(1, stride(C,2))
5125 # Do checks
5126 chkuplo(uplo)
5127 if length(e_) != n - 1
5128 throw(DimensionMismatch("off-diagonal has length $(length(e_)) but should have length $(n - 1)"))
5129 end
5130 if ncvt > 0 && ldvt < n
5131 throw(DimensionMismatch("leading dimension of Vt, $ldvt, must be at least $n"))
5132 end
5133 if ldu < nru
5134 throw(DimensionMismatch("leading dimension of U, $ldu, must be at least $nru"))
5135 end
5136 if size(U, 2) != n
5137 throw(DimensionMismatch("U must have $n columns but has $(size(U, 2))"))
5138 end
5139 if ncc > 0 && ldc < n
5140 throw(DimensionMismatch("leading dimension of C, $ldc, must be at least $n"))
5141 end
5142 # Allocate
5143 work = Vector{$relty}(4n)
5144 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
5145 ccall((@blasfunc($bdsqr), liblapack), Void,
5146 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5147 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{$elty},
5148 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
5149 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
5150 &uplo, &n, &ncvt, &nru,
5151 &ncc, d, e_, Vt,
5152 &ldvt, U, &ldu, C,
5153 &ldc, work, info)
5154 chklapackerror(info[])
5155 d, Vt, U, C #singular values in descending order, P**T * VT, U * Q, Q**T * C
5156 end
5157 end
5158 end
5159
5160 """
5161 bdsqr!(uplo, d, e_, Vt, U, C) -> (d, Vt, U, C)
5162
5163 Computes the singular value decomposition of a bidiagonal matrix with
5164 `d` on the diagonal and `e_` on the off-diagonal. If `uplo = U`, `e_` is
5165 the superdiagonal. If `uplo = L`, `e_` is the subdiagonal. Can optionally also
5166 compute the product `Q' * C`.
5167
5168 Returns the singular values in `d`, and the matrix `C` overwritten with `Q' * C`.
5169 """
5170 bdsqr!(uplo::Char, d::StridedVector, e_::StridedVector, Vt::StridedMatrix, U::StridedMatrix, C::StridedMatrix)
5171
5172 #Defined only for real types
5173 for (bdsdc, elty) in
5174 ((:dbdsdc_,:Float64),
5175 (:sbdsdc_,:Float32))
5176 @eval begin
5177 #* DBDSDC computes the singular value decomposition (SVD) of a real
5178 #* N-by-N (upper or lower) bidiagonal matrix B: B = U * S * VT,
5179 #* using a divide and conquer method
5180 #* .. Scalar Arguments ..
5181 # CHARACTER COMPQ, UPLO
5182 # INTEGER INFO, LDU, LDVT, N
5183 #* ..
5184 #* .. Array Arguments ..
5185 # INTEGER IQ( * ), IWORK( * )
5186 # DOUBLE PRECISION D( * ), E( * ), Q( * ), U( LDU, * ),
5187 # $ VT( LDVT, * ), WORK( * )
5188 function bdsdc!(uplo::Char, compq::Char, d::StridedVector{$elty}, e_::StridedVector{$elty})
5189 chkstride1(d, e_)
5190 n, ldiq, ldq, ldu, ldvt = length(d), 1, 1, 1, 1
5191 chkuplo(uplo)
5192 if compq == 'N'
5193 lwork = 6*n
5194 elseif compq == 'P'
5195 warn("COMPQ='P' is not tested")
5196 #TODO turn this into an actual LAPACK call
5197 #smlsiz=ilaenv(9, $elty==:Float64 ? 'dbdsqr' : 'sbdsqr', string(uplo, compq), n,n,n,n)
5198 smlsiz=100 #For now, completely overkill
5199 ldq = n*(11+2*smlsiz+8*round(Int,log((n/(smlsiz+1)))/log(2)))
5200 ldiq = n*(3+3*round(Int,log(n/(smlsiz+1))/log(2)))
5201 lwork = 6*n
5202 elseif compq == 'I'
5203 ldvt=ldu=max(1, n)
5204 lwork=3*n^2 + 4*n
5205 else
5206 throw(ArgumentError("COMPQ argument must be 'N', 'P' or 'I', got $(repr(compq))"))
5207 end
5208 u = similar(d, $elty, (ldu, n))
5209 vt = similar(d, $elty, (ldvt, n))
5210 q = similar(d, $elty, ldq)
5211 iq = similar(d, BlasInt, ldiq)
5212 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5213 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(8n)
5214 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
5215 ccall((@blasfunc($bdsdc), liblapack), Void,
5216 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
5217 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5218 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}),
5219 &uplo, &compq, &n, d, e_,
5220 u, &ldu, vt, &ldvt,
5221 q, iq, work, iwork, info)
5222 chklapackerror(info[])
5223 d, e, u, vt, q, iq
5224 end
5225 end
5226 end
5227
5228 """
5229 bdsdc!(uplo, compq, d, e_) -> (d, e, u, vt, q, iq)
5230
5231 Computes the singular value decomposition of a bidiagonal matrix with `d` on the
5232 diagonal and `e_` on the off-diagonal using a divide and conqueq method.
5233 If `uplo = U`, `e_` is the superdiagonal. If `uplo = L`, `e_` is the subdiagonal.
5234 If `compq = N`, only the singular values are found. If `compq = I`, the singular
5235 values and vectors are found. If `compq = P`, the singular values
5236 and vectors are found in compact form. Only works for real types.
5237
5238 Returns the singular values in `d`, and if `compq = P`, the compact singular
5239 vectors in `iq`.
5240 """
5241 bdsdc!(uplo::Char, compq::Char, d::StridedVector, e_::StridedVector)
5242
5243 for (gecon, elty) in
5244 ((:dgecon_,:Float64),
5245 (:sgecon_,:Float32))
5246 @eval begin
5247 # SUBROUTINE DGECON( NORM, N, A, LDA, ANORM, RCOND, WORK, IWORK,
5248 # $ INFO )
5249 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
5250 # CHARACTER NORM
5251 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, N
5252 # DOUBLE PRECISION ANORM, RCOND
5253 # * ..
5254 # * .. Array Arguments ..
5255 # INTEGER IWORK( * )
5256 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), WORK( * )
5257 function gecon!(normtype::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, anorm::$elty)

5260 lda = max(1, stride(A, 2))
5261 rcond = Vector{$elty}(1)
5262 work = Vector{$elty}(4n)
5263 iwork = Vector{BlasInt}(n)
5264 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
5265 ccall((@blasfunc($gecon), liblapack), Void,
5266 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5267 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5268 Ptr{BlasInt}),
5269 &normtype, &n, A, &lda, &anorm, rcond, work, iwork,
5270 info)
5271 chklapackerror(info[])
5272 rcond[1]
5273 end
5274 end
5275 end
5276
5277 for (gecon, elty, relty) in
5278 ((:zgecon_,:Complex128,:Float64),
5279 (:cgecon_,:Complex64, :Float32))
5280 @eval begin
5281 # SUBROUTINE ZGECON( NORM, N, A, LDA, ANORM, RCOND, WORK, RWORK,

5284 # CHARACTER NORM

5286 # DOUBLE PRECISION ANORM, RCOND
5287 # * ..
5288 # * .. Array Arguments ..
5289 # DOUBLE PRECISION RWORK( * )
5290 # COMPLEX*16 A( LDA, * ), WORK( * )

5302 Ptr{BlasInt}),
5303 &normtype, &n, A, &lda, &anorm, rcond, work, rwork,
5304 info)
5305 chklapackerror(info[])
5306 rcond[1]

5311 """
5312 gecon!(normtype, A, anorm)
5313
5314 Finds the reciprocal condition number of matrix `A`. If `normtype = I`,
5315 the condition number is found in the infinity norm. If `normtype = O` or
5316 `1`, the condition number is found in the one norm. `A` must be the
5317 result of `getrf!` and `anorm` is the norm of `A` in the relevant norm.
5318 """
5319 gecon!(normtype::Char, A::StridedMatrix, anorm)
5320
5321 for (gehrd, elty) in
5322 ((:dgehrd_,:Float64),
5323 (:sgehrd_,:Float32),
5324 (:zgehrd_,:Complex128),
5325 (:cgehrd_,:Complex64))
5326 @eval begin
5327
5328 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
5329 # INTEGER IHI, ILO, INFO, LDA, LWORK, N
5330 # * ..
5331 # * .. Array Arguments ..
5332 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), TAU( * ), WORK( * )
5333 function gehrd!(ilo::Integer, ihi::Integer, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
5334 chkstride1(A)
5335 n = checksquare(A)
5336 chkfinite(A) # balancing routines don't support NaNs and Infs
5337 tau = similar(A, $elty, max(0,n - 1))
5338 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
5339 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
5340 info = Ref{BlasInt}()

5342 ccall((@blasfunc($gehrd), liblapack), Void,
5343 (Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
5344 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5345 Ptr{BlasInt}),
5346 &n, &ilo, &ihi, A,
5347 &max(1, stride(A, 2)), tau, work, &lwork,
5348 info)
5349 chklapackerror(info[])
5350 if i == 1
5351 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5352 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5353 end
5354 end
5355 A, tau
5356 end
5357 end
5358 end
5359 gehrd!(A::StridedMatrix) = gehrd!(1, size(A, 1), A)

5430 function ormhr!(side::Char, trans::Char, ilo::Integer, ihi::Integer, A::StridedMatrix{$elty},
5431 tau::StridedVector{$elty}, C::StridedVecOrMat{$elty})

5441 throw(DimensionMismatch("A and C matrices are not conformable"))

5460 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)

5468 for (gees, gges, elty) in
5469 ((:dgees_,:dgges_,:Float64),
5470 (:sgees_,:sgges_,:Float32))
5471 @eval begin
5472 # .. Scalar Arguments ..
5473 # CHARACTER JOBVS, SORT
5474 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDVS, LWORK, N, SDIM
5475 # ..
5476 # .. Array Arguments ..
5477 # LOGICAL BWORK( * )
5478 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), VS( LDVS, * ), WI( * ), WORK( * ),
5479 # $ WR( * )
5480 function gees!(jobvs::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})
5481 chkstride1(A)
5482 n = checksquare(A)
5483 sdim = Vector{BlasInt}(1)
5484 wr = similar(A, $elty, n)
5485 wi = similar(A, $elty, n)
5486 vs = similar(A, $elty, jobvs == 'V' ? n : 0, n)
5487 ldvs = max(size(vs, 1), 1)
5488 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
5489 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
5490 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
5491 for i = 1:2
5492 ccall((@blasfunc($gees), liblapack), Void,
5493 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{Void}, Ptr{BlasInt},
5494 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},

5498 A, &max(1, stride(A, 2)), sdim, wr,
5499 wi, vs, &ldvs, work,
5500 &lwork, C_NULL, info)
5501 chklapackerror(info[])
5502 if i == 1
5503 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5504 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5505 end
5506 end
5507 A, vs, iszero(wi) ? wr : complex.(wr, wi)

5509
5510 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..
5511 # CHARACTER JOBVSL, JOBVSR, SORT
5512 # INTEGER INFO, LDA, LDB, LDVSL, LDVSR, LWORK, N, SDIM
5513 # * ..
5514 # * .. Array Arguments ..
5515 # LOGICAL BWORK( * )
5516 # DOUBLE PRECISION A( LDA, * ), ALPHAI( * ), ALPHAR( * ),
5517 # $ B( LDB, * ), BETA( * ), VSL( LDVSL, * ),
5518 # $ VSR( LDVSR, * ), WORK( * )
5519 function gges!(jobvsl::Char, jobvsr::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty}, B::StridedMatrix{$elty})
5520 chkstride1(A, B)
5521 n, m = checksquare(A, B)
5522 if n != m
5523 throw(DimensionMismatch("dimensions of A, ($n,$n), and B, ($m,$m), must match"))
5524 end
5525 sdim = BlasInt(0)
5526 alphar = similar(A, $elty, n)
5527 alphai = similar(A, $elty, n)
5528 beta = similar(A, $elty, n)
5529 ldvsl = jobvsl == 'V' ? n : 1
5530 vsl = similar(A, $elty, ldvsl, n)
5531 ldvsr = jobvsr == 'V' ? n : 1
5532 vsr = similar(A, $elty, ldvsr, n)
5533 work = Vector{$elty}(1)
5534 lwork = BlasInt(-1)
5535 info = Ref{BlasInt}()
5536 for i = 1:2
5537 ccall((@blasfunc($gges), liblapack), Void,
5538 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{Void},
5539 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
5540 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty},
5541 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty},
5542 Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{Void},
5543 Ptr{BlasInt}),
5544 &jobvsl, &jobvsr, &'N', C_NULL,
5545 &n, A, &max(1,stride(A, 2)), B,
5546 &max(1,stride(B, 2)), &sdim, alphar, alphai,
5547 beta, vsl, &ldvsl, vsr,
5548 &ldvsr, work, &lwork, C_NULL,
5549 info)
5550 chklapackerror(info[])
5551 if i == 1
5552 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5553 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5554 end
5555 end
5556 A, B, complex.(alphar, alphai), beta, vsl[1:(jobvsl == 'V' ? n : 0),:], vsr[1:(jobvsr == 'V' ? n : 0),:]
5557 end
5558 end
5559 end

5561 for (gees, gges, elty, relty) in
5562 ((:zgees_,:zgges_,:Complex128,:Float64),
5563 (:cgees_,:cgges_,:Complex64,:Float32))
5564 @eval begin

5571 # DOUBLE PRECISION RWORK( * )

5573 function gees!(jobvs::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty})

5576 sort = 'N'
5577 sdim = BlasInt(0)

5580 ldvs = max(size(vs, 1), 1)

5593 vs, &ldvs, work, &lwork,

5595 chklapackerror(info[])
5596 if i == 1
5597 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5598 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5599 end
5600 end
5601 A, vs, w
5602 end
5603
5604 # * .. Scalar Arguments ..

5607 # * ..

5609 # LOGICAL BWORK( * )

5633 (Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{UInt8}, Ptr{Void},

5637 Ptr{$elty}, Ptr{BlasInt}, Ptr{$relty}, Ptr{Void},
5638 Ptr{BlasInt}),
5639 &jobvsl, &jobvsr, &'N', C_NULL,
5640 &n, A, &max(1, stride(A, 2)), B,
5641 &max(1, stride(B, 2)), &sdim, alpha, beta,
5642 vsl, &ldvsl, vsr, &ldvsr,

5644 info)
5645 chklapackerror(info[])
5646 if i == 1
5647 lwork = BlasInt(real(work[1]))
5648 work = Vector{$elty}(lwork)
5649 end
5650 end

5652 end
5653 end

5656 """
5657 gees!(jobvs, A) -> (A, vs, w)
5658
5659 Computes the eigenvalues (`jobvs = N`) or the eigenvalues and Schur
5660 vectors (`jobvs = V`) of matrix `A`. `A` is overwritten by its Schur form.

5663 eigenvalues.

5672 vectors (`jobsvl = V`), or right Schur vectors (`jobvsr = V`) of `A` and
5673 `B`.

5676 vectors are returned in `vsl` and the right Schur vectors are returned in `vsr`.
5677 """

5783 end

5972 """
5973 trexc!(compq, ifst, ilst, T, Q) -> (T, Q)
5974
5975 Reorder the Schur factorization of a matrix. If `compq = V`, the Schur
5976 vectors `Q` are reordered. If `compq = N` they are not modified. `ifst`
5977 and `ilst` specify the reordering of the vectors.
5978 """
5979 trexc!(compq::Char, ifst::BlasInt, ilst::BlasInt, T::StridedMatrix, Q::StridedMatrix)
5980
5981 """
5982 trsen!(compq, job, select, T, Q) -> (T, Q, w)
5983
5984 Reorder the Schur factorization of a matrix and optionally finds reciprocal
5985 condition numbers. If `job = N`, no condition numbers are found. If `job = E`,
5986 only the condition number for this cluster of eigenvalues is found. If
5987 `job = V`, only the condition number for the invariant subspace is found.
5988 If `job = B` then the condition numbers for the cluster and subspace are
5989 found. If `compq = V` the Schur vectors `Q` are updated. If `compq = N`
5990 the Schur vectors are not modified. `select` determines which
5991 eigenvalues are in the cluster.
5992
5993 Returns `T`, `Q`, and reordered eigenvalues in `w`.
5994 """
5995 trsen!(compq::Char, job::Char, select::StridedVector{BlasInt}, T::StridedMatrix, Q::StridedMatrix)
5996
5997 """
5998 tgsen!(select, S, T, Q, Z) -> (S, T, alpha, beta, Q, Z)
5999
6000 Reorders the vectors of a generalized Schur decomposition. `select` specifices
6001 the eigenvalues in each cluster.
6002 """
6003 tgsen!(select::StridedVector{BlasInt}, S::StridedMatrix, T::StridedMatrix, Q::StridedMatrix, Z::StridedMatrix)
6004
6005 for (fn, elty, relty) in ((:dtrsyl_, :Float64, :Float64),
6006 (:strsyl_, :Float32, :Float32),
6007 (:ztrsyl_, :Complex128, :Float64),
6008 (:ctrsyl_, :Complex64, :Float32))
6009 @eval begin
6010 function trsyl!(transa::Char, transb::Char, A::StridedMatrix{$elty},
6011 B::StridedMatrix{$elty}, C::StridedMatrix{$elty}, isgn::Int=1)
6012 chkstride1(A, B, C)
6013 m, n = checksquare(A, B)
6014 lda = max(1, stride(A, 2))
6015 ldb = max(1, stride(B, 2))
6016 m1, n1 = size(C)
6017 if m != m1 || n != n1
6018 throw(DimensionMismatch("dimensions of A, ($m,$n), and C, ($m1,$n1), must match"))
6019 end
6020 ldc = max(1, stride(C, 2))
6021 scale = Vector{$relty}(1)
6022 info = Ref{BlasInt}()

6035
6036 """
6037 trsyl!(transa, transb, A, B, C, isgn=1) -> (C, scale)
6038
6039 Solves the Sylvester matrix equation `A * X +/- X * B = scale*C` where `A` and
6040 `B` are both quasi-upper triangular. If `transa = N`, `A` is not modified.
6041 If `transa = T`, `A` is transposed. If `transa = C`, `A` is conjugate
6042 transposed. Similarly for `transb` and `B`. If `isgn = 1`, the equation
6043 `A * X + X * B = scale * C` is solved. If `isgn = -1`, the equation
6044 `A * X - X * B = scale * C` is solved.
6045
6046 Returns `X` (overwriting `C`) and `scale`.
6047 """
6048 trsyl!(transa::Char, transb::Char, A::StridedMatrix, B::StridedMatrix, C::StridedMatrix, isgn::Int=1)
6049
6050 end # module
